Commentary: OUT! BOWLED! Can you believe it? That's Ashes for you! Mitchell Starc you beauty! He draws first blood and roars. Starc seams in and bowls it full and on leg. Rory Burns shuffles across too far, tries to flick but misses and gets knocked round his legs. There might be hint of late swing as well. This is a dramatic start as it gets. A wicket of the first ball and Australia are delighted. The players are all over Mitchell Starc. Rory Burns has to take the long walk back and goes without troubling the scorers. England certainly didn't hope for this kind of start. An early blow to them. Welcome to the 'Gabba' says Starc.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: FOUR! England and Dawid Malan are underway! This is full and around off, hint of away swing. Dawid Malan without any foot movement looks to defend but this goes off the outer half and through the gully region for a boundary.
A full ball, on middle. Dawid Malan defends it towards cover.
Fuller in length, on off. Malan opens his face of the bat and hits it through point for a couple of runs.
A length ball, outside off. Malan blocks it to point.
A length ball, on middle. Malan stays back and tucks it to square leg.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping in. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone.
JAFFA! Back of a length, around off, nipping in. Haseeb Hameed this time tries to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed covers the line and blocks it down with a dead bat.
Haseeb Hameed gets off the mark! Good-length ball, on middle. No movement off the ball this time. Haseeb Hameed tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, in the fourth stump channel, nipping away from the batter. Good bounce and carry as well. Dawid Malan watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Just the single off the over then! Josh Hazlewood again hurls in a back-of-a-length ball, on middle this time. Dawid Malan stands up on his toes and defends it down the pitch.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Haseeb Hameed lets it sal through.
Fuller in length, outside off. Haseeb Hameed leans onto it and drives but finds the cover fielder.
Length ball, outside off. An easy leave for Haseeb Hameed.
FOUR! That's a shot! Pure timing and placement! Fuller in length, on off. Haseeb Hameed gets into the position early and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Starc drags his length a bit this time, outside off, shaping away. Haseeb Hameed lets it go.
Good-length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to that one.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Dawid Malan leaves it for the keeper to collect.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Alex Carey takes his first catch on his debut and England lose their second wicket. Josh Hazlewood serves a good-length ball, around off, with a hint of away movement. Enough to kiss the outside edge of Dawid Malan's bat as he has a poke at it. Alex Carey makes no mistake behind the stumps as it was a regulation catch. Dawid Malan has to walk back to the pavilion and Australia are all pumped as they have got two wickets very early into this game.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Josh Hazlewood

Commentary: Full and on off, shaping back in. Joe Root plays that one back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off, shaping back in again. Joe Root taps it towards covers.
Length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Joe Root presses forward and steers it to point.
Huge inward movement! Back of a length, on off. The ball rises on that occasion and shaped back in sharply. Joe Root looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. A wicket-maiden from Josh Hazlewood.
Back of a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge and falls short of the man at second slip.
Length ball, on off, coming back in sharply. Haseeb Hameed is caught in the crease as he tries to defend and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Pitched up, outside off, Haseeb Hameed shuffles across a bit before making a leave.
Slightly fuller, on the off pole. Haseeb Hameed pats it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle. Haseeb Hameed watches it closely and meets it with a dead bat.
Back of a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed gets on top of the ball and blocks it from the crease.
A length ball, outside off. Root shoulders arms to it.
On a length and angling on middle. Joe Root hops and defends it on the leg side.
BEATEN! Beauty. A full ball, outside off, this one hits the deck and shapes away. Root prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one nips back in sharply. A length ball, on middle. Root stays back to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.

OUT! TAKEN! Australia not letting England to settle in. What a start for the Aussies. A full ball, outside off, this one is coming with the angle. Joe Root lunges and looks to block it out but the ball takes the outside edge and it goes straight to the first slip where David Warner holds onto it. England in all sorts of trouble as their skipper goes on a duck.
Howout: c David Warner b Josh Hazlewood

Commentary: Short of a length, angling across, outside off. Stokes shoulders arms to it.
JAFFA! Back of a length, outside off. Haseeb Hameed looks to play it but leaves it very late. Good leave actually.
Fuller ball, on off. Hameed gets on the front foot to keep it out.
Full again, on off. Hameed blocks it towards cover.
Now serves Hameed with a short ball. Haseeb Hameed sits under it.
BEATEN! A full ball, just around the fifth stump channel. Haseeb Hameed looks to defend on the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off. Hameed punches it with soft hands through covers and takes a couple of runs.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Stokes shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on middle. Ben Stokes is strong behind the line of the ball as he defends it out.
Another solid defence from Stokes. This is on a length and on middle.
A length ball, outside off. Stokes shuffles across and leaves it alone. Good from Stokes, he just need to stay in the middle for some time.
Ben Stokes is off the mark. A full ball, on middle, flicked to square leg. He slips as he flicks but no harm done as he completes the run comfortably.
LEG BYE! Short of a length, angling on the thigh pad. Haseeb Hameed misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to square leg and a leg bye is taken.
On a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed nudges it to deep square leg for one run.
Full ball, on middle. Ben Stokes covers his stumps and blocks it out.
That one really stayed low. A length ball, angling on off. Ben Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Back of a length, on middle, tucked away to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Ben Stokes rocks back and defends it solidly.
A length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
A length ball, swinging in, on middle. Haseeb Hameed watches carefully and defends it on the leg side.
FOUR! Edgy runs! A full ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed looks for a big booming drive but gets a thick outside edge over the slip cordon and the ball races away to the third man fence.
On a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed hops and taps it on the off side.

A full ball, on middle. Haseeb Hameed drives it straight back. Mitchell Starc seems to get a hand on it as the ball ricochets it on the non-striker's stumps and Australia appeal for a run out but the umpire is not interested in it.
A length ball, on the hip. Defended out.
Back of a length, outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it alone to the keeper.
Fuller in length, on the pads. Ben Stokes clips it to short mid-wicket.
OH! That was close! Good-length ball, angling in on middle. Ben Stokes lets it go. The ball goes just over the middle stump and carries through to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Ben Stokes presses forward and drives it to mid off. Travis Head there does well to dive to his left and stop the ball. Saved a certain boundary.
On a good length, on middle, angling in. Ben Stokes turns it to short mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on middle. Ben Stokes stays solid in his defence.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes is not troubled by that line as he shoulders arms to that one. A maiden from Pat Cummins!
FOUR LEG BYES! Back of a length, on leg. Haseeb Hameed looks to tuck but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads and races away to the fine leg fence for four leg byes.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Haseeb Hameed lets it sail through. This is much better line from Starc.
What a ripper! Tad fuller, in the fourth stump channel, swinging away. Haseeb Hameed is forced to have a poke at it but gets fortunate as it beats his outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Haseeb Hameed leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Haseeb Hameed watches it let go past him.
Fuller this time, on off. Haseeb Hameed puts a stride forward and drives it well but straight to the mid off fielder. A dot to end the over!
Fuller in length, at 136 kph, on off. Ben Stokes drives it confidently but straight to mid off.
FOUR! Well played! Pat Cummins pitches it up, outside off. Ben Stokes leans onto it, opens the face of the bat and drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Ben Stokes taps it to the off side.
WIDE! Cummins bangs in too short, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes sways away from the line. Wide called for height.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pat Cummins gets rid of the big fish. Hurls in and bowls a back-of-a-length ball, on middle, angling in. Ben Stokes gets all squared up and hops from his crease as he tries to defend. The ball kisses the outside edge and flies to the third slip where Marnus Labuschagne takes a good low catch diving to his left. Ben Stokes is not happy with that and goes back shaking his head off. First wicket for Pat Cummins and Australia well on top! England in deep deep trouble now!
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Off the mark straighaway! Full and outside off. Ollie Pope gets forward and pushes it towards covers for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Haseeb Hameed ducks underneath.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope shoulders arms to that one.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Around off, on a length, coming back in. Ollie Pope lets it through.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg, coming back in. Ollie Pope looks to defend but gets struck on the thigh pad.
Fuller in length this time, on middle. Ollie Pope drives it straight back to the bowler. Josh Hazlewood collects it on his followthrough and gives a stare to the batsman.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Left alone. Another maiden for Josh Hazlewood!
On a good length, on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it awkwardly. The ball goes off the bottom half of the bat towards short fine leg for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Ollie Pope pulls it towards deep square leg. Didn't hit it quite from the middle of the bat and the batter gets three runs.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hameed leaves it untouched.
Good-length ball, outside off. No movement there. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms.
On a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed covers the line and blocks it out.
Fuller in length, on off. Haseeb Hameed wrists it to deep mid-wicket. Long chase for Mitchell Starc who runs from mid on and cuts it off. Three runs taken. 7 runs coming from the over.
A length ball, on middle. Hameed tucks it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Pope covers his stumps and lets it through to the keeper.
Another outside off delivery, another easy leave for Pope.
This is short and around off. Ollie Pope ducks under it.
A length ball, on off. Pope hangs back and blocks it on the off side.
Angles a length ball, on off. Pope defends it confidently.
A length ball, targeting the pads, hint of seam movement. Haseeb Hameed misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Short of a length, angling across, around off. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms to it.
On a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed glances it to the fine leg region for a single.
FOUR! Good shot. A length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it through the square on the off side and bags his first boundary.
On a length, on middle, swinging in very late. Ollie Pope gets an inside edge as he looks to defend and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full ball, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length, just around off. Haseeb Hameed covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, slanting on middle. Haseeb Hameed solidly blocks it out.
Length and on off. Another solid defense from Haseeb Hameed on the off side.
This was on a length and way outside off. Left alone.
On a length, on off. Haseeb Hameed hops and blocks it to point.
A length ball, just around off. Haseeb Hameed looks to defend inside the line but gets beaten on the outside edge. Maiden over.
On middle, on a length. Ollie Pope blocks it off the upper half of the blade back on the deck.
A length ball, on middle. Pope turns it to the on side.
Length and on off. Ollie Pope hits it back to the bowler. Solid defensive intent from Pope.
Touch fuller, outside off, pushed straight to covers.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A full ball, outside off. Ollie Pope gets on his knee and drives it through the vacant cover region for a boundary.
Now targets the pads, Pope tucks it to square leg.
Lyon starts with a tossed up ball, on middle. Haseeb Hameed rocks back and blocks it towards short leg.
Flatter and outside off. Hameed taps it to point.
Full and on off. Haseeb Hameed defends it off the front foot.
A loopy ball, on middle. Hameed hangs back and blocks it back on the surface.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Haseeb Hameed prods and keeps it out.
Quicker one now, on middle. Haseeb Hameed rocks back and nudges it to square leg. Maiden to start for Nathan Lyon.
Back of a length, on middle. Ollie Pope looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Good-length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope shoulders arms to that one.
On a good length, on middle. Ollie Pope tucks it to square leg and scampers across for a quick single.
Length ball, on middle, straightens up after pitching. Haseeb Hameed looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Starc bangs in short, on middle. Haseeb Hameed negotiates with that one easily by ducking under it.
Back of a length, on off, with a slight inward movement. Haseeb Hameed drops it to the off side and retains the strike by taking a single.
Fllighted, full and on off. Haseeb Hameed nudges it to mid on for a tight single. 50 up for England!
Tossed up, on off. Ollie Pope blocks it out from the crease.
Loopy ball, on off. Ollie Pope steps out and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Full and on middle, Ollie Pope uses his feet to defend it to mid on.
Short and on middle. Ollie Pope pulls but the ball hits Marnus Labuschagne at short leg.
Outside off, Ollie Pope makes room for himself and cuts it straight to cover-point.

Green starts with a fuller length, down the leg side. Haseeb Hameed looks to flick but misses. The ball brushes off his pads and carries through to the keeper. Australia appeal for a catch but the umpire says no.
Fuller, outside off. Driven towards covers.
Very full, on middle. Haseeb Hameed flicks it straight to square leg.
Bangs in short, on middle. Haseeb Hameed sits under it.
Good-length ball, on off. Haseeb Hameed is solid in his defence.
Fuller in length, on off. Haseeb Hameed drives it to short cover. A maiden to begin with for Cameron Green!
Tossed up nicely, on middle. Ollie Pope presses forward and defends it out.
Short and on off, some turn there as well. Ollie Pope hangs back and defends it to the off side off the outer half of the bat.
On middle, blocked out.
Short and outside off, cut away to point.
Short again, on middle. Ollie Pope hits it through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Nicely played! Loopy ball, around off. Haseeb Hameed rocks back and dabs it past first slip towards third man for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone by Pope.
Fuller in length, on off. Pope drives it straight to cover.
Full again, on the pads this time. Ollie Pope flicks it to deep square leg to collect a couple of runs.
Touch fuller, on middle. Pope nudges it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope shoulders arms.
A full toss, down the leg side. Ollie Pope looks to flick but misses.
Loopy ball, on middle. Haseeb Hameed plays it with the turn towards covers for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and tries to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. A mild appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Short and on middle, Ollie Pope comes down the track and hits it to deep square leg. One.
Floated it up, on off. Hameed blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Hameed is solid in his defence.
Full and on off, Haseeb Hameed presses forward and negotiates well by defending it back onto the deck. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
A length ball, angling on middle. Ollie Pope mistimes as he looks to play on the leg side.
A full ball, outside off. Pope prods and defends it towards cover for a quick single.
A length ball, outside off, shaping a bit away, Haseeb Hameed looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! Haseeb Hameed's long stay in the middle comes to an end. A length ball, angling outside off. Haseeb Hameed gets on the front foot to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards the second slip where Steven Smith takes a sharp catch on his left. Half of the England side back in the hut.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Full and angled in, pushed to covers.
Length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it from the crease. A great start for Australia post Lunch. A wicket and a single off it.
A full ball, outside off. Ollie Pope punches it through covers for a quick single.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling! This is on a length and around off. Jos Buttler looks to drive but gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball passes over the stumps.
A length ball, outside off. Jos Buttler keeps it out.
FOUR! Jos Buttler is off the mark now. Over-pitched delivery, outside off. Buttler drives it firmly through covers for a boundary.
Full again, outside off. Buttler this time punches it to covers and takes a couple of runs.
A pacy short ball, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Pope taps it to covers for a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Buttler punches it through covers for a single. England finding the gaps and taking quick singles here.
A short ball, banged on middle. Ollie Pope misses his pull and the keeper jumps to grab it.
Outside off, on a length, pushed to point.
This one shoots off the deck. Short of a length, on off. Pope looks to defend but gets hit on the right tricep. That was quick as well.
On a length, outside off. Pope taps it to the gully fielder.
FOUR! Jos Buttler is not in a mood to play defensive strokes. A full ball, outside off. Butter drives it on the up and clears mid off for a boundary.
A length ball, way outside off. Left alone.
Again outside off, an easy leave for Buttler.
This one nips back in, on a length, on off. Jos Buttler blocks it on the leg side.
A length ball, just around off. Jos Buttler defends it as he gets on his toes.
A full ball, on middle. Jos Buttler lifts it over mid on. The ball bounces near the ropes and the mid on fielder cuts it off in time. Three taken.
PEACH! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Jos Buttler looks to drive but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Length ball, on middle. Jos Buttler defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Jos Buttler blocks it out.
Nice batting from Buttler! Back of a length, on off. Jos Buttler punches it through covers. The point fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
More runs! Fuller, on middle. Ollie Pope flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple more.
Good-length ball, on middle. Ollie Pope covers the sticks and defends it back to the bowler.
Little fuller, outside off. Jos Buttler shoulders arms.
Full again, on off. Jos Buttler looks to drive but gets an outside edge to point.
This is good counter-attack from Buttler! This was on a length, on off. Jos Buttler lofts it towards long off. Travis Head from mid off gives it a chase and the batters run three.
On a length, on middle. Ollie Pope tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Jos Buttler works it through mid-wicket for a brace now.
On a good length, on off. Jos Buttler taps it to point.
Short of a length, on middle. Ollie Pope pulls it to deep backward square leg. There's protection in the deep and will only get a single.
Back of a length, on off. Jos Buttler punches it to mid off.
Back of a length, slanting into the batter. Jos Buttler looks to work it on the leg side but gets struck on the thigh pad.
FOUR! He is timing the ball so well! Widh offered, outside off. Jos Buttler pounces on it and carves it to deep backward point for a boundary.
Full and angled in, Jos Buttler taps the ball to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Jos Buttler taps it to point off the back foot.
Well fielded! Back of a length, on off. Ollie Pope guides it towards gully. The fielder there does well to dive to his right and stop the ball.
Fuller, on off. Pushed towards covers for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Jos Buttler stays solid in his defence.
Good-length again, outside off. Jos Buttler is not interested to offer a shot to that.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Jos Buttler clips the ball off his pads to deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Length ball, on middle. Pope blocks it to mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off, nipping away. Loose shot from Jos Buttler as he tries to drive it on the up but fails to connect.

NOT OUT! Good-length ball, down the leg side. Jos Buttler looks to flick but misses. Alex Carey grabs the ball and throws it in the air in delight as he thinks Buttler has nicked it. Australia appeal but the umpire says no. Pat Cummins opts for a review. No mark on the HotSpot and the on-field decision stays. Replay shows that it came off the thigh pad and hence, Australia were interested. They burn their review though.
Good-length ball, on middle. Jos Buttler defends it out.
Fuller, on off. Buttler pushes it to mid off.
Length ball, on off. Buttler pushes it towards covers.
A touch fuller, on middle. Jos Buttler drives it back to the bowler. A maiden over!
Angles a full ball, on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter, slower and outside off. Buttler hits it back to the bowler.
Slightly short and on middle. Buttler rocks back and pushes it back to the bowler.
This one spins back in, on middle. Jos Buttler tucks it on the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Full and outside off, turning back in. Ollie Pope prods as he defends with bat and pad together. A muted appeal follows for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
On middle, on a length, Blocked out.
Full ball, on middle. Buttler flicks it to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single.
Short ball, on middle. Pope pulls it to deep backward square leg where Josh Hazlewood does well to stop it. Along with that single, 100 comes up for England. A good passage of play from the visitors.
A length ball, on middle. Buttler solidly blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off. Buttler drives it straight to short cover where Marnus Labuschagne catches it on a bounce.
A length ball, down the leg side. Buttler misses his flick.
A flatter ball, outside off. Pope cuts it through backward point. The fielder gives a long chase and flicks it back near the ropes. Three runs.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Quicker one, on middle. Buttler rocks back and blocks it on the deck.
FOUR! Good shot! A loopy ball, on off. Jos Buttler drives it crisply and through covers for a boundary.
Lyon comes 'round the wicket and serves a full ball, on middle. Buttler solidly defends it.
Full again, on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
A length ball, way outside off. Pope shoulders arms to it.

Short of a length, on middle, Pope tucks it to mid-wicket and scampers across for a quick single. The fielder there dives and flicks it on the non-striker's end but Pope made his crease with a big dive.
A bouncer now, on middle. Buttler sits under it.
A length ball, on middle, tucked on the leg side.
Length and on middle. Defended out.
Short again, on middle. Jos Buttler sways away from the line of the ball.
Tossed up, on off. Ollie Pope comes down the track and defends it out off the front foot.
Full and on off. Pope solidly blocks it.
Sharp turn again, tossed up, around middle. Ollie Pope rocks back to flicked it but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
A flighted ball, on middle. Ollie Pope lunges to defend.
Slightly short and outside off. Pope cuts it straight to point.
Good-length ball, on middle. Jos Buttler tucks it on the leg side.

FOUR! Crunched away! Widh on offer, outside off. Mitchell Starc latches onto it and carasses it through covers for a boundary. That brings up the 50-run partnership as well between Jos Buttler and Ollie Pope.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Second catch for Alex Carey on his debut and he commits no mistake. Just when the partnership was starting to blossom for England, Jos Buttler holes out. Mitchell Starc provides his team with a breakthrough. Serves a good-length ball, on off, nipping away. Jos Buttler has a nibble at it from his crease. The ball goes off the outside edge and goes to Alex Carey who gobbles it up cleanly. Huge wicket as Jos Buttler was looking dangerous.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes lets it sail through.
Back of a length, on off. Chris Woakes prods and defends it from the crease.
Fuller in length, outside off. Chris Woakes drives it through covers for a couple of runs to get off the mark. A sucessful over from Mitchell Starc as he gets rid of Jos Buttler.
Loopy ball, on off. Pope blocks it on the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Pope blocks it watchfully.
Nicely played! Full and outside off, Ollie Pope pushes it through covers for a couple of runs.
Turning in, on leg. Pope is solid in his defence.
Around off, pushed to cover.
Floated it up, on middle. Pope nudges it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, on off. Ollie Pope presses forward and defends it solidly off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Ollie Pope tucks it on the leg side for a run.
Length ball, outside off, pushed to covers.
Bangs in short, on middle. Chris Woakes sways away from the line and half-ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Chris Woakes hops and blocks it right under his eyes.
Width offered, outside off. Chris Woakes drives it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a catch from Josh Hazlewood in the deep! Cameron Green bags his maiden Test wicket and enters the wickets column as well. Green bowls a back-of-a-length delivery, on middle. The ball gets a little too big for Ollie Pope as he tries to pull. He is slightly late on his shot and the ball goes off the top edge towards deep backward square leg. Josh Hazlewood has to cover quite a ground as he runs from fine leg and runs to his left. He keeps his eyes on the ball, makes a full-stretch dive and manages to grab the ball. A stunner from him. Cameron Green is elated and so is Australia! They have been all over England.
Howout: c Josh Hazlewood b Cameron Green

Commentary: Serves a short ball, on middle. Woakes sits under it.
FOUR! Well played! This was on a length and outside off. Chris Woakes drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a length, on off, Blocked out.
A full ball, on middle. Chris Woakes turns it to square leg.
A successful over from Cameron Green. This was around off. Woakes taps it on the off side.
Bangs in short, on middle. Ollie Robinson sits under it.
Length ball, on leg. Flicked to short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another catch for Alex Carey. He is having a day out and so is their new skipper as he bags his third. Pitches it on a good length, outside off, nipping away. Ollie Robinson is tempted to go for a drive. The ball goes off the outside edge and carries through to Alex Carey who snaffles it up. England in nothing but tatters now.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Mark Wood looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, angling in, on off. Mark Wood looks to defend but gets an insideedge onto the pads.
Full, outside off, shaping away. Mark Wood goes feeling for it but gets beaten on the outside edge. A wicket-maiden from Pat Cummins.
Serves a length ball, on middle. Chris Woakes blocks it out.
Alex Carey appeals behind for caught behind but Hazlewood shakes his head. A length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on middle. Chris Woakes defends it on the deck.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A full ball, on off. Chris Woakes drives it with soft hands and wide of mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! A length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and beats the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! Three boundaries in a row! A length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes dabs it late and through the slip cordon for a boundary.
A full ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length, on middle. Mark Wood pulls it to square leg for a couple. Marnus Labuschagne gives the chase and cuts it off.
FOUR! Boundaries flowing with ease! Full and on off. Mark Wood drives it crisply wide of mid off for a boundary.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Mark Wood sways away from the line.
A length ball, on middle. Wood defends it under his eyes.
Short of a length, on middle. Wood gets hit on the gloves as he attempts to block.
Length and outside off, punched to point for a single.
Length ball, way outside off. Wood leaves it alone.
A length ball, angling on middle. Wood defends it solidly.
In the air but safe! A short ball, on middle. Mark Wood rides the pull and hits it to vacant deep square leg region for a brace.
Length and around off. Kept out.
Length again, outside off. Wood taps it straight to gully.
Short of a length, angling down the leg side. Woakes swings and misses.
A length ball, on off. Woakes taps it to point for a quick single.

OUT! TAKEN! Cummins goes wide of the crease and serves a short-of-a-length ball, on middle. Mark Wood hops and looks to work it on the leg side but without any control. He gets hit on the gloves and the ball lobs nicely for Marcus Harris who takes the easiest of catches at short leg.
Howout: c Marcus Harris b Pat Cummins

Commentary: An appeal for caught behind but turned down! A length ball, outside off. Leach looks to defend but misses.
On a length, on off. Leach blocks it on the off side.
A full ball, on off. Leach punches it wide of mid off and gets off the mark with a couple of runs.
Tossed up, outside off. Woakes prods and defends it out.
Outside off. Woakes skips down and drills it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Leach gets on the front foot to block it out.
Now covers his stumps and blocks it to covers.
Full and on off. Kept out.
Leach survives. Around off, defended to point.

OUT! TAKEN! The captain takes a five-fer. A short ball, on middle. Chris Woakes pulls it but does not middle it. The ball goes off the top edge towards Josh Hazlewood in the deep again. He has to work hard as he runs across from fine leg and takes a diving catch. He plucks it just above the ground. Almost a carbon copy of the catch he took at backward square leg of Pope. Sensational stuff from Josh Hazlewood and England are all out for 147. THAT WILL ALSO BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Howout: c Josh Hazlewood b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Australia and David Warner are underway. A length ball, on off. Warner taps it to point and runs for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but instead hits it to Warner.
Short of a length, on middle. Harris stands tall and blocks it out. Good bounce from Woakes.
Short again and on middle. Harris stands behind the line of the ball and defends it on the surface.
Marcus Harris is off the mark as well! A length ball, outside off. Harris leans into his drive and hits it through covers for a brace. Confident-looking drive that from Harris!
Now targets the hip area. Harris stays back and tries to nudge it away. Gets hit on the body though. No swing or seam noticed yet.
On a length, on off. Harris punches it through point for a single. Both Australian openers off to a confident start.

Robinson starts with a length ball, angling outside off. Harris looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Only the slip cordon is appealing for a caught behind but Ollie Robinson shakes his head.
A length ball, on off. Harris works it with an angled bat to gully.
Touch fuller, on middle. Harris defends it off the front foot to covers.
BEATEN! Good bowling from Robinson. This one jags away after landing, Harris is squared up as he looks to defend it out.
On a length, outside off. Harris covers his stumps and shoulders arms to it.
Length and on middle. Harris blocks it back to the bowler. Maiden to start for Ollie Robinson.
JAFFA! Woakes goes fuller now, outside off. Warner does not move too much as he tries to defend it. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
A length ball, on middle. Warner prods and defends it back to the bowler. Chris Woakes collects the ball and mimes a throw as Warner is made to race back to the crease.
Full and on the pads, flicked to the left of mid-wicket where the fielder dives and stops it. A single.
Length ball, outside off. Positive leave from Marcus Harris.
Another leave from Harris as he prods across and shoulders arms to this full ball.
Short of a length, outside off, extra bounce on offer. Harris lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball but this is way outside off. Easy leave for Warner.
A length ball, straight and on middle. David Warner solidly blocks it out.
Outside off again, on a length. Warner steps across and shoulders arms to it.
On a length and on middle. Warner hangs back and punches it back to the bowler.
Robinson concedes his first run. A full ball, on middle. Warner punches it with soft hands to mid off and scampers across for a quick single.
BEATEN! Good finish to the over. This is on a length and just around the 4th stump channel. Harris has a poke at it but misses as the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
FOUR! The sound it made when the ball hit the blade. Brilliant. A length ball, outside off. David Warner drives it firmly through mid off for a boundary. Helds his pose as well.
Short and outside off. Warner sways away from it.
Way outside off, on a length. Left alone.
Short and on middle. Warner with another good leave as he leans back and lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, outside off. David Warner leaves it alone to the keeper.
Dot to end the over! On a length, on middle. Warner blocks it on the deck.
Good-length ball, in the fourth stump channel. Marcus Harris shoulders arms.

OUT! CAUGHT! England needed an early breakthrough and Ollie Robinson provides them with one. Hurls a good-length ball, outside off, nipping away. Marcus Harris has a feel for it. The ball kisses the outside edge and flies to the third slip. Dawid Malan moves to his left and takes a good low catch. Ollie Robinson roars as he draws first blood. Good start by them and Marcus Harris has to walk back to the pavilion for a timid score.
Howout: c Dawid Malan b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good-length ball, around off. Got some extra bounce as well. Marnus Labuschagne moves away and lets it through.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drills it to point.
Pitched up, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail through.
Ohh, that was close! Full again, very close to the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne at first thinks of playing it but in the end, opts out as he shoulders arms.
Short of a length from around the wicket, outside off. David Warner offers no shot to that.
Short of a length again, on middle. David Warner hops and taps it to the off side for a single.
Some serious pace there from Wood! Short of a length, on middle, at 147.2 kph. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it onto the deck.
Good-length delivery, around off, at 150 kph. Marnus Labuschagne watches the ball closely and leaves it untouched.
Length ball, outside off, at 151.6 kph. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it for the keeper to collect.
This is a little fuller, in the corridor of uncertainty. Marnus Labuschagne is not interested in playing that. Just a single off the over then.
Good-length ball, angling away from off. David Warner shoulders arms to it.

Fuller in length, on the pads. David Warner flicks it to mid-wicket for a tight single. Chris Woakes quickly moves to his left, picks the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. The batsman was well in though.

FOUR! Good-length ball, around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge and races past the slip cordon to third man for a boundary. Few words exchanged between them.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Touch fuller, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it towards covers.
FOUR! Shot! Fuller in length, on off, at 130 clicks. Marnus Labuschagne this time drives it past mid off. Ben Stokes gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the boundary.
Just short! Back of a length, on off. David Warner chips it uppishly towards extra cover. The ball falls just short of Ben Stokes there.
On a length, on off. David Warner taps it to point.
Length ball, outside off. Warner pushes it straight to point.
Good bouncer from Wood! Bangs a short ball, hard onto the deck, on middle. David Warner sits under it.
Good-length ball, on middle, angling in. David Warner pushes it to point.
Swing and a miss! Good-length ball, well outside off. David Warner goes chasing for it and has a hard swing at it but fails to connect. A maiden!
Good-length ball, around off, nipping in. Marnus Labuschagne makes a good leave.
In the corridor of uncertainty, no swing this time. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through.
Good-length ball, coming into the batter, on leg. Marnus Labuschagne looks to tuck but gets hit on the pads. An appeal from the keeper for an lbw but the umpire says no. Probably going down leg.
Length ball, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards point. He calls for a single and starts running but David Warner sends him back and rightly so. A maiden over from Woakes!
Wood continues from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, just around off. Warner tries to cut it but this was too close to cut.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
Body blow! A length ball, angling on middle. David Warner rocks back as he looks to flick but gets beaten by the pace. Gets hit on the body.
Swing and a miss! Short of a length, outside off. Warner looks to cut it again but misses it completely.
Quick single! A length ball, on middle. Warner taps it in front of covers and scampers through for a single.
Length and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket.
A full ball, straight on middle. David Warner pushes it nicely straight down the ground before the fielder cuts it off. Three taken.
A length ball, on off, defended back on the deck.
A length ball, way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms to it.
Outside off delivery, on a length. Marnus Labuschagne with yet another leave.
Angles this one on middle. Marnus Labuschagne watchfully defends it.
Over-pitched from Woakes and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne frees his arms as he drives it through covers and picks up a couple of runs.
A length ball, on middle. David Warner gets an inside edge onto the pads as he looks to flick and the ball rolls to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Just wide of the slip fielder! A length ball, outside off. David Warner looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes through the left of third slip for a boundary.
Very full, on middle. Blocked out.

NO BALL! It looked like Ben Stokes knew it was a no ball even before the umpire signals it as Stokes walk back on his mark. This was full and on middle. David Warner gets beaten on the inside edge as he looks to defend but misses and the ball sneaks through and rattles the stumps. Warner survives as the umpire signals a no ball as Stokes overstepped.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball and way outside off. Warner watchfully leaves it alone.
Full ball, on off, Warner works it to mid off.
A length ball, on middle, Blocked out.
Just short of the first slip. A full ball, angling around off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to push but it takes the outside edge to Joe Root at first slip who collects it on a bounce.
Short and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it, not quite of the middle though. Hits it over mid-wicket and collects three runs.
On a length, on off. David Warner hops and blocks it to covers.
A length ball, on middle. David Warner solidly defends it out.
Now goes full, on middle. David Warner defends it off the front foot.
Full and way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.

Quick single! A full ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it in front of covers and takes a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Would have been close if that hit the stumps.
WIDE! A pacy short ball, on middle. David Warner watches it sail over his head. Wide given for height.
Short of a length, on off. Warner covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Length and on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Length and on off, defended to covers. Warner is quick to call no to his partner.
An appeal for LBW but that was clearly pitching outside leg. A length ball, on the pads. David Warner misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Good-length ball, on middle, coming back in. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms and gets hit above the pads.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail through.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket for a run.
On a length, angling away, outside off. David Warner leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lucky boundary! Good-length ball, on middle, angling away. David Warner looks to defend it with soft hands. The ball goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon for a boundary.
PEACH! Good-length ball, nipping away from middle. David Warner looks to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. A fine delivery to end the over.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Well outside off, Marnus Labuschagne is not troubled by that line and lets it be.
Short, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it untouched.
Short of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne hops and blocks it from the crease. No ball signalled as Ben Stokes overstepped.
Fuller, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne continues his leaving spree.
Good-length ball, around off, angling away. David Warner watches the ball closely and shoulders arms.
On a good length, in the fourth stump channel. Warner lets it be.
Good-length ball, on leg. David Warner pushes it to mid off.
JAFFA! Good-length ball, around off, nipping away from middle. David Warner presses forward and looks to defend. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
Back of a length, on middle. Warner defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on middle. Warner hops and taps it towards covers and shouts 'no run'.
Fuller, on middle, at 148.7 kph. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it on the leg side.
That one moves away! Good-length ball, on off, moving away. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. That was a beauty from Mark Wood.
Back of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked back to the bowler.
Wood goes wide on the crease this time and bowls it full, on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it on the off side.
Very full, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to drive but misses.
Back of a length, on middle. Warner hops and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, on middle. Warner plays it to mid off.
Fuller in length, outside off. Warner lets it go.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller in length from 'round the wicket, on off. David Warner prods, opens the face of the bat and creams it through extra cover and mid off for a boundary.
Switches to over the wicket again, on a length, on middle. Warner looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
In the channel, outside off. Left alone.
Dot ball!
Dot ball!
Dot ball!
Dot ball!
Dot ball!
Dot ball!
One run!
Dot ball!
Three taken!
Short of a length, on middle. David Warner hops and looks to tuck but gets hit on the body.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On a length, on middle. David Warner blocks it on the off side.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne misses his flick and gets hit on thigh pad. The ball rolls to fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
A length ball, on middle. David Warner flicks it just over short leg and collects a couple of runs.
A length ball, on off. David Warner defends it towards cover and takes a quick single.
A length ball, on off, kept out.
A length ball, angling on the pads, flicked through mid-wicket and three runs are taken as the fielder cuts it off near the fence.
Length and on off, defended out.
Full ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it through covers and picks up another three runs. This also brings up a 50-partnership between these two.
A length ball, outside off. Warner cuts it through point. The fielder chases it and cuts it off. Three.
FOUR! Runs flowing now for Australia. Pitches it up, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leans and drives it through covers and collects a boundary.
BEATEN! This one shapes away after landing, on a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on middle, pulled to square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle. Defended out.
Starts with a tossed up ball, on middle, driven to mid off.
Full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne wrists it to square leg for a single.
Very full and outside off. David Warner smashes it straight back to the bowler. Leach in a little bit of pain.
A loopy ball, outside off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and on middle. David Warner blocks it out.
Fuller ball, on middle. David Warner defends it off the front foot.
Fraction straighter and fuller, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms.
On a length, on middle. Tucked to mid-wicket for an easy single.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner hops and fends it to cover.

Ripper! Good-length ball, on off, nipping away. The ball shoots up after landing. David Warner looks to defend but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. That was a beauty from Woakes!
LEG BYE! On the pads, tickled to backward square leg off the pads for a leg bye.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it to mid-wicket.
SIX! Warner wants to attack Leach! In the slot, on middle. David Warner stands tall and lofts it over long on for a maximum. Attacking intent rightaway!
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
SIX! Here he goes again! Loopy ball, on middle. David Warner advances down the track and hammers it over long on for another biggie of the over. He moves to 44 with that shot.
Tosses it up, on middle. Warner pushes it to covers.
Shortish, on leg. Warner makes room and punches it towards point for a single.

FOUR! Now Marnus Labuschagne gets in the act! This is pushed wider and fuller, Marnus Labuschagne leans onto it and creams it through covers for a boundary. A forgettable over for Leach. 17 runs coming from it.
Good-length ball, on off. Warner lets it go.
Back of a length, on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
On a length, on leg. Pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR BYES! Length ball, outside off. Warner shoulders arms to that one. The ball just dies after pitching and Jos Buttler dives to his left to collect the ball but couldn't. It sneaks through his gloves and into the fence for four byes.
On a good length, outside off. Warner leaves it alone.
SWING AND A MISS! Good-length ball, outside off. David Warner has a hard swing at it but fails to connect.
A full ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets low and drives it through covers for three runs. The Aussies targeting Leach here.
Full and outside off. David Warner comes down the track and hits it back to the bowler.
Very full and off. David Warner paddles it to the fine leg region for a single.
SIX! 100 up for Australia! A full ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne skips down and tonks it over long on for a biggie. He moves to 44 now.
On middle. Marnus Labuschagne advances down and smacks it back to Leach. He half-stops it and doesn't allow any run.
Misfield! A full ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to covers where Ben Stokes lets it through. He chases it and flicks it back in the deep. Till that time, three taken.
FOUR! FIFTY for Marnus Labuschagne. He just loves batting here at Gabba. A length ball, outside off, cut away to point for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne hops and taps it to point.
A 100-run partnership between Warner and Labuschagne! Length and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
Length again, outside off. David Warner shoulders arms.
Full ball, on off, pushed to covers.
A length ball, slanting outside off. David Warner watchfully leaves it.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it to backward point.
Short and angling down the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it to the keeper.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne taps it late on the off side.
Fuller ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it towards cover and takes a quick single.
BEATEN! Short of a length, just around the channel of uncertainty. David Warner looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Two taken! This was full and outside off. David Warner awkwardly cuts it through the diving point fielder and collects a brace. That will be Lunch on Day 2.
A full ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne prods and blocks it towards cover.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Full and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne flicks it to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single. First run of this session.
BEATEN! Lovely bowling! On a length, outside off. David Warner looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Warner has a big smile on his face.

DROPPED at second slip! A full ball, slanting outside off. David Warner looks to push it but gets a thick outside edge to the left of the second slip where Rory Burns fumbles to catch it and puts down a dolly. A single. Second reprieve to Warner. How costly will this prove to be?
On middle, on a length, blocked on the leg side.
Starts from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, angling on middle. David Warner looks to block but gets hit on the body.
Short ball, angling down the leg side. David Warner misses his pull.
A length ball, on middle. Warner defends it on the surface.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Warner looks to cut but misses.
Short in length, outside off. Warner lets it through.

FIFTY for David Warner! He continues his great form. A length ball, outside off. David Warner punches off the back foot through covers for three runs. A wonderful knock from Warner and will look to convert this into a bigger one. Loud applause from the crowd as well as he raises his bat.
A length ball, on middle. Warner defends it off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Length and slanting outside off. Warner shoulders arms to it.
Short ball, around off. Left alone.
Serves it in the channel of around off. David Warner watchfully leaves it.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on off, Warner defends it out.
Now Wood serves it around the fourth stump line and keeps it tight. Marnus Labuschagne covers his stump and shoulders arms.
This one jags back in very late. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone to the keeper.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it on middle, tucked to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Pulled away! Comes around the wicket and bangs it short. David Warner pulls it wide of the running square leg fielder for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. David Warner looks to defend with an angled bat but misses it.
Length and on middle. David Warner taps it to point and looks for a quick single but was wisely sent back. Dot ball.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, angling in, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Fuller in length, on middle. Driven back past the bowler. The mid on fielder moves to his left and stops the ball.
Very well-judged leave! On a good length, coming back in, on off. Marnus Labuschagne watches the ball closely and lets it through.
Good-length ball, around off, coming back in. ML leaves it for the keeper to collect. A maiden!
Fuller in length, attacking the stumps at 152 clicks. Warner defends it out.
Into the blockhole, at 152 clicks again. Warner jams it out.
WIDE! Bangs in way short, on off. Warner tries to pull but misses. The keeper collects it over his head. Wide called for height.
Back of a length, on middle. Warner stays solid in his defence.
Back of a length again, on middle. Warner hops and taps it to point.

FOUR! Superb shot! Back of a length yet again, on leg this time, trying to get Warner cramped for room. David Warner instead makes room for himself by moving that side and cuts it through point for a boundary.

Was that a run out chance? Full and on middle, Warner prods and nudges it to short leg. He then slips and loses his control over his bat as well trying to make it back to the crease. Warner ends up crawling back to the crease. Haseeb Hameed at short leg has ample time to score a direct hit at the stumps but he misses from a short distance. Warner gets another lifeline!
Short and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne stands up on his toes and meets the ball with a dead bat.
Length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through.
Too straight, outside off. Left alone by Marnus.
Fuller in length, on off. Pushed to mid on.
Short of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Warner taps it to point.
Fuller in length, on off. Warner pushes it to mid off.
On a length, around off. Warner shouders arms.
Good-length ball, in the channel, outside off. Left alone.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Warner nudges it to square leg.
Back of a length, on middle. Warner hops and blocks it out. A maiden!
Length ball on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to square leg for a single.
Fuller in length, on middle. Warner knocks it back to the bowler.
On a good length, outside off. Warner offers no shot.
Good-length ball, outside off. Warner drops his bat and leaves it alone.
FOUR! That was four from the moment it left the blade. Length ball, outside off. David Warner smashes it through covers. The ball races away to the boundary in a flash.
Outside off, Warner lets it sail through.
A length ball, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne watchfully lets it through.
Touch fuller, on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne wrists it to mid-wicket and beats the diving fielder there. Two.
FOUR! Nicely played! Another full ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it uppishly and through square leg for a boundary.
Short and outside off. Left alone.
Tossed up on middle, flicked to square leg.
Full and on middle. Warner makes room and drives it to wide long off for a single.
Full and on off. Marnus Labuschagne skips down and hits it to the left of Leach who fails to stop it and the mid off fielder cuts it off. One.
This one lands on middle and spins away from the left-hander. David Warner tries to reverse sweep it but misses.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Slightly short and on off. David Warner solidly defends it.
Length and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it out.
On a length, on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! This one nips away and draws Marnus Labuschagne to drive but gets comprehensively beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on middle. Marnus sits under it.
A length ball, on off. Defended out.
Slower ball, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it under his eyes.
Shorter and on the pads. Warner nudges it to square leg.
Darted on the pads, flicked to fine leg for a single.
Flatter, slower and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne skips down and drives it to deep point for a brace.
This is wide outside off. Left alone.
A loopy ball, on off, Marnus Labuschagne turns it on the leg side for a single.
Short and on the pads, Warner flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Short in length and on middle. David Warner pulls it all along the ground to backward square leg where the fielder does well to run to his right and stop it. Two. Australia lead by one run now.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, outside off,  steered to point.
Full ball, outside off. Warner leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. Warner punches it to point for a single.
On middle, tucked to deep square leg for a single. 150 up for Australia!
Loopy ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Well played! Tossed up, on middle. David Warner gets down on his knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary. Australia are not allowing Jack Leach to settle.
This is nudged to square leg.
On middle and leg. Warner deefnds it out.
Shortish and on leg, Warner drops it to short fine leg off the back foot.
Loopy ball, on middle. Warner uses his feet and drills it long on for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. David Warner drills it past mid off for a coupls of runs.
Back of a length, on off. Warner taps it to point off the front foot.
On a good length, on off. Warner gets on top of the bounce and pushes it to mid off.
Fuller in length, on middle. Warner clears his front leg and drives it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Warner first decides to leave. But in the end, fends it off the bottom half of the bat to gully.
Width on offer, full and outside off. David Warner reaches out for it and plays it through cover-point for a couple of runs. The partnership between these two is now 150!
SIX! SMACKED! Loopy ball, on off. Marnus Labuschagne shimmies down the track and muscles it over long off for a maximum. Courageous batting this! Jack Leach continues to be expensive.

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket out of nowhere and England get a much-needed breakthrough and it's Jack Leach who has provided that. Bowls it tad short, on off. Marnus Labuschagne hangs back, makes room for himself and cuts it straight to backward point. The ball perhaps got too big on him. Mark Wood there grabs the catch and Marnus Labuschagne walks off the pitch after a fine innings. Huge applause from the crowd as well. Can England build on this now?
Howout: c Mark Wood b Jack Leach

Commentary: Full and outside off. Smith lunges forward and pats it back to the bowler.
FOUR! No respect to the bowler from Steven Smith as well. Opens his account with a boundary. This was full and on leg, Steven Smith dances down the track and whips it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, Smith defends it to extra cover.
Quicker, on the stumps. Smith defends it to short mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Warner hops and fends it away to point.
Length ball, on leg. Warner plays it on the leg side.
FOUR! He continues on his merry way! Fuller, outside off. Warner pierces the gap between point and cover and gets a boundary.
Back of a length, on leg. Warner gets up on his toes and tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Length ball on leg, Smith tucks it to short leg.
Fuller, on middle. Smith nudges it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, on middle. Pushed to extra cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! This is tossed up, on middle. David Warner gets down on one knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
On leg, turning away. Warner pads it away.
Drops it short, on middle. Pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Smith puts a big stride forward and blocks.

In the air, but safe! Loopy ball, on off, turning away. Steven Smith advances down the track and looks to loft it over covers. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies over backward point. Ollie Robinson gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.

NOT OUT! A length ball, coming with the angle on off. Steven Smith looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge and gets hit on the back pad. An appeal but nothing from the umpire. Mark Wood has a discussion with his skipper and convinces him to opt for the review. HotSpot shows no bat. Ball tracker shows the impact was outside off and the on-field decision stays. England lose their review.

Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket. Smith runs across for a quick single but gets hesitant with Wood standing on his way. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Was gone by a miles if that had hit!
Short and on middle, pulled away to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short and on middle. Smith ducks underneath.
This is on a length and way outside off. Left alone.
BEATEN! On a length and outside off. Warner looks to defend but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off. Warner punches off the back foot to covers.
Length again, outside off. Warner lets it through.
This is on a length and outside off, extra bounce and it beats the outside edge of Warner.
Full and way outside off. Warner shoulders arms.
A length ball, slanting across, outside off. Warner leaves it alone.
Full ball, on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Smith stands tall and punches it to covers.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Goes wide of the crease and bowls a full ball, outside off. Smith shuffles and drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Short and on leg. Smith sits under it.
A length ball, on middle. Smith defends it to mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mark Wood gets his man and the big-gun, Smith goes for a timid score. Back of a length, outside off. Smith has an unnecessary poke at it. He only manages an outside edge and Jos Buttler pouches it with ease. No need for Smith to chase that one as he was just settling in. Australia lose their third now.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Mark Wood

Commentary: On a length, on off. Warner hops and blocks it out.
Length again, outside off, Warner shoulders arms.
FOUR! Edgy runs! David Warner moves to 94! A full ball, outside off. David Warner tries to defend but gets an outside edge and beats the diving third slip for a boundary.
Fuller ball, on off. Kept out.
A length ball, way outside off. Warner makes a leave.
Dot to end the over. Length ball, around off. Warner covers his stumps and lets it through to the keeper. That will be TEA on Day 2.
Good-length ball, on off. Head covers the line and defends it out.
Ohhh! Back of a length, outside off. Travis Head hops and looks to go over covers but only connects it with thin air round him.
Back of a length again, on middle. Head hops and blocks it out.
Back of a length yet again, on middle. Head jumps and fends it on the leg side this time. Mark Wood falls on his followthrough but is fine to continue.
Length ball, on off. Head taps it towards covers and scampers across to get off the mark.
Length ball, on leg. Warner looks to tuck but misses. Gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls to fine leg. The batters take a leg bye.
On a length, on middle. Warner pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Would you believe it? Warner misses out on a century. Robinson hurls in and bowls a slower ball, on middle. The ball stops a bit on the surface. David Warner tries to push it towards covers but throws his hands too early. He chips it instead towards extra cover where Ben Stokes dives ahead to catch the ball. Devastation for David Warner as he walks back to the pavilion after an excellent knock. For the first time in seven occasions, David Warner failed to hit a century after being dismissed off a no ball in a Test innings.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Sensational stuff from Ollie Robinson and England are back in the contest. Serves a good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Cameron Green comes forward and just shoulders arms to that one. Probably didn't read the length well. The ball jags back in and shatters the stumps. That was not a good leave at all. England are all pumped up and Ollie Robinson is on a hat-trick now. Alex Carey is the new batsman in.
Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: No hat-trick for Ollie Robinson! Length ball, on middle. Carey blocks it out.
Back of a length, on leg. Carey deflects it off his pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
Back of a length, on middle. Head defends it onto the deck. Superb over from Ollie Robinson!
Length ball, outside off. Carey throws the kitchen sink at it but fails to connect.
Good-length ball, on middle. Alex Carey tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On a good length, on middle. Carey blocks it from the crease.
Short of a length, on middle. Alex Carey negotiates with it well by swaying away from the line.
Back of a length, on middle. Carey covers his sticks and defends it from the crease.
Length ball, on off. Carey stays solid in his defence.

FOUR! EDGY! Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Travis Head looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat too early. The ball goes off the outside edge and goes past the slip cordon and gully for a boundary. Travis Head is very fortunate there. Five slips and a gully and the ball still finds the gap!
Fuller this time, on off. Head presses forward and defends it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, on off. Head gets all squared up and manages a thick outside edge to the fifth slip fielder.
Good-length ball, on off. Head tries to leave it alone but is late in lifting his bat. The ball goes off the bottom edge and drops on the ground.
A length ball, on middle. Travis Head stays back and defends it out.
Slower ball, on the pads. Head flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Back of a length, on middle. Head defends it out off the front foot.
Good-length ball, on off, nipping away. Travis Head looks to defend but misses. The ball whistles past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, on middle. Head defends it with a dead bat.
Length ball, outside off. Head taps it towards covers.
Short of a length, on off. Head pushes it to point and shouts 'no run'.
On a good length, on middle. Head stands up on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Well blocked! Good-length ball, angling across. Carey presses forward and knocks it back to the bowler.
Touch fuller, outside off, angling away. Carey shoulders arms to that one.
Fuller, on the pads. Carey nudges it to square leg.
FOUR! First runs for Alex Carey in Test cricket! Opens his account with a boundary. This was full, on off. Alex Carey drives it towards long off for a boundary.
And again! Carey drives this full ball again to long off. The mid off fielder gives it a chase and manages to keep it down to three runs.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Robinson sprays this one on the pads, Travis Head flicks it through mid-wicket. The mid-wicket fielder gives it a long chase and prevents the ball racing away to the boundary but the batters have run four already.
A length ball, angling across, outside off. Carey shoulders arms to it.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Carey looks to cut but fails to get any bat on it.
Length again, outside off. Carey leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a length, on middle. Carey blocks it out.
A length ball, on middle. Carey works it to mid-wicket.
Just short of the third fielder. A length ball, outside off. Carey looks to push but gets an outside edge to the third slip where the fielder dives forward and collects it on a bounce.
Short of a length, on middle. Head gets on his toes as he tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Pulled away! Short of a length, on middle. Head hangs back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Now through the off side. A length ball, outside off. Head cuts it through point for another boundary. Turning out to be a good over for Australia.
Short of a length, on middle. Head defends it on the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Punched to covers.

FOUR! Third boundary of the over! On a length, on middle. Head pulls it to deep square leg. Jack Leach runs across to his right, puts a dive and flicks it but the ball rolls back and touches the fence.
A length ball, outside off. Carey lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, on middle. Carey looks to flick but gets hit on the gloves. The ball lobs and drops back on the deck.
On a length, on middle. Carey solidly blocks it out.
Length again, on middle. Carey tucks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Pitches it up, on off. Head pushes it more off the outer half of the bat towards cover-point for a single.
Three taken! A short ball, outside off. Carey slashes onto it, not quite off the middle towards deep cover and the batters take three runs.
Starts with a very full ball, on off, pushed down to long off for a single.
Tossed up, on off, Carey drives it to covers.
Again pushes it but straight to covers. Dot.
A full ball, angling around leg. Alex Carey tries to reverse sweep it to the fine leg region for a single. Buttler puts up an appeal for LBW but that came off the blade.
Around off, pushed to covers.
SIX! BANG! A loopy ball, outside off. Head tonks it all the way over long on for a biggie.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Angles a length ball, on middle. Carey gets on the front foot and defends it out.
Full and outside off. Carey prods across and shoulders arms to it.

OUT! TAKEN! England finds another breakthrough and Carey's debut innings is cut short for a timid score. Short of a length, on middle. Alex Carey gets on his toes as he looks to wrists it to mid-wicket but finds Ollie Pope at short mid-wicket who shows good reflexes and grabs this one over his head. Australia lead by 89 runs and England hanging in there.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Welcomes Cummins with a fuller ball, on middle. Cummins defends it out.
Full again, angling on middle. Pat Cummins nudges it on the leg side. A successful over from Chris Woakes, wicket-maiden over.
Short and outside off, Head rocks back and scythes it through cover-point for three runs.
Loopy ball, on leg. Cummins tucks it on the leg side.
Fuller this time, on the pads. Cummins blocks it out on the leg side.
Down the leg side, turning away. Cummins lets it be.
Again down the leg side. Cummins pads it away this time.
Loopy ball down leg yet again. Cummins leaves it untouched.
Good-length ball, on middle. Head covers the line and knocks it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
A bouncer this time, on middle and leg. Head sits under it.
Fuller in length, around off. Head doesn't move his feet much and looks for a drive. Only manages to get an inside edge onto the pads.
Good-length ball, on off. Head defends it from the crease.
Back of a length, on off. Head hops and looks to defend but misses. He gets hit right above the elbow and looks to be in some pain.
Back of a length, on middle. Tucked to backward square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Head cuts it through point for a couple of runs.
Full and on off. Head prods and smashes it back to the bowler. Root collects it and mimes a throw at him.
Outside off, cut away to point.
Tossed up, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
On middle. Head rocks back and looks to defend. Gets an inside edge and the ball rolls on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on middle. Head eases it down to long on for a single.
Short of a length, outside off. Head punches it to mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Head jumps up on his toes and blocks it out.
FOUR! Head moves into the 40s! A full ball, outside off. Head slashes it hard and through the point region for a boundary. A little bit of the late Phillip Hughes in that shot.
Back of a length again, on off. Head hops and fends it away to the off side. Wood looking tired now!
On middle, Head pushes it to mid on.
Fuller in length, pushed wider. Travis Head latches on it and drives it through cover-point for an easy two.
Loopy ball, on middle. Cummins presses forward and defends it out.
Good shot for three! Tossed up, on middle. Pat Cummins lifts it over covers. Long chase for the cover fielder and the batters take three runs.
Floats it up, on leg. Travis Head tucks it on the leg side.

FOUR! Edgy! Loopy ball, on middle. Travis Head steps out and looks to cut. The ball goes off the outside edge and goes past the keeper's gloves to third man for a boundary. Moves onto 46 now! Bit strange from Root and Leach. They have a leg slip for Head but no conventional slip. Had that conventional slip been there, it would have gone straight to him. Possibly because Leach has been expensive, it has forced Root to go defensive and it has cost them a potential wicket. That too, of the last recognized batter.
Drags his length back and bowls it on leg, Travis Head works it to backward square leg for a single.
Drifting it on leg, Cummins is solid in his defence.
FOUR! FIFTY for Travis Head, his 8th Test fifty and he is controlling the innings well really well. A full toss, on off. Head drives it firmly and through covers for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Head taps it to the gully region where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
Short of a length, outside off. Cummins watchfully leaves it.
Serves a pacy bouncer on middle. Cummins sits under it.
A length ball, outside off. Cummins looks to defend but gets an outside edge and the ball rolls along the ground to the slip fielder.
Angles a length ball, on middle, tucked to square leg.
Flatter and on middle. Head nudges it to square leg and takes an easy single.
Tossed up, on middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Full and on middle. Head leans and wrists it to the leg side.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

MISFIELD, FOUR! Oopsy, what happened there? Short, around leg, Head pulls it to deep backward square leg. There are shouts of 'CATCH IT!' but Haseeb Hameed over there does not spot the ball at all. He looks to his left, then his right and in the end, realizes that the ball is coming at him. Runs forward but the ball bounces in front of him and worse, hits his body and deflects behind. It lobs in the air and Hameed looks to stop it off the rebound but too late, the ball is beyond the ropes! Oh dear, that is right in front of a vocal 'Gabba crowd and it is cheering!

FOUR! Full and down the leg side. Head gets on his knee and sweeps it past the leg slip for a boundary. Poor ball but England will not mind that too much. They need Cummins to face Wood and try and take wickets.
Fuller in length, outside off. Cummins drives it firmly but straight to the cover fielder.
Full again, on off, little slower this time. Cummins pushes it on the off side.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Cummins looks to heave it away but gets hit on the thigh pads. A muted appeal for an lbw from the keeper but the umpire says no.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Cummins pushes it to mid on.
Fuller, on middle. Cummins flicks it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Down the leg side. Cummins looks to flick but misses.
Loopy ball, outside off. Head punches it to deep point off the back foot for a single. Much better line from Leach!
Loopy ball, on off. Pat Cummins puts a big stride forward to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to third man. Haseeb Hameed gives it a chase and cuts it off. Two taken.
On off, punched to mid off for a single.
SIX! MASSIVE! Tosses it up, on middle. Travis Head comes down the track and hammers it over the bowler's head for a biggie.

FIVE RUNS! Oh dear! Full and outside off. Head comes down the track and smashes it to mid off for a single. Ben Stokes collects the ball and has a shy at the keeper's end. Pat Cummins makes his ground with a dive. The throw is a wild one and it goes past Jos Buttler and dribbles away into the fence. Jack Leach is not happy with that at all.
Flatter and angling on middle. Cummins lunges and blocks it out.
Full and on middle. Head pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Head punches it to covers.
Short ball, on off. Head sits under it.
NO BALL! A length ball, angling on middle. Head misses his flick and gets hit high on the pads. Ben Stokes oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
FOUR! A length ball, on middle. Head smashes it wide of mid on and bags a boundary for himself.
FOUR! Top edge and the ball rolls away to the fence! A short ball, on middle. Head looks to pull but gets a top edge and races away behind the keeper for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Travis Head is taken aback by the bounce. He does well though to drop it to the off side and take a single. 10 runs off the over.
Full ball, on off. Head skips down and pushes it to long off for a single. 300 up for Australia!
Three taken! Full ball, outside off. Pat Cummins makes room and gets low, lifts this one over covers for three runs.
Short and outside off, cut away to covers for a brace.
A loopy ball now. Head works it to deep cover for a single.
Follows Cummins on the leg side and serves it full, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! Australia 7 down now. A full ball, down the leg side. Pat Cummins flicks it late with soft hands towards the leg slip where Haseeb Hameed is stationed and he takes a good low catch. Pat Cummins is disappointed with himself as he walks back. The England skipper gets the opponent skipper! End of a crucial 70-run stand.
Howout: c Haseeb Hameed b Joe Root

Commentary: Short of a length, around off. Head looks to cut but gets cramp for room and misses.
Short and on middle. Head sits under it.
Short of a length, on off. Head again gets cramp for room as he looks to cut.
Short and on middle. Head ducks under it.
Full and on middle, drilled down to long off for a single.
Immediately off the mark! Length ball, on off. Starc nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full ball, on off. Starc gets low and pushes it on the off side for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Head looks to slog-sweep but gets a top edge over the keeper's head and they take two runs.
A low full toss, Head drives it to deep cover. Malan there runs across and dives but fumbles to collect it but does enough to flick it back with his leg. Three.
Tossed up, on off, pushed to covers.
Full and on middle. Starc pushes it to covers.
Slightly short outside off. Starc taps it to point.
Length ball, on off. Head pushes it through covers for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Starc watches the ball closely and lets it go.
Good-length ball, outside off. Starc with an another leave.
On a good length, on middle. Starc pushes it to cover.
Short ball, on off. Starc takes his eyes off the ball and pulls it without any timing to mid-wicket. A single is taken.

Short of a length, on middle. Travis Head hops and taps it towards covers. He wanted to be on strike the next over and thus sprins across for a quick single. Haseeb Hameed has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Good running!
Short and on off. Head punches it to wide of deep mid-wicket. The fielder moves to his right and cuts it off. Keeps it down to two runs.
This is pushed back to the bowler.
