Loopy ball, on middle. Travis Head looks to work it on the leg side. He gets hit on the forearm and the ball lobs up in the air behind the keeper on the leg side. Rory Burns moves to his right and dives forward to take the catch but it didn't come off the gloves.
Full and on middle. Head eases it down to long on for a single.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fired in, on leg. Starc looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no. Going down leg.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away as well. Left alone.

FOUR! There it comes! FIRST ASHES HUNDRED FOR TRAVIS HEAD! What a knock this has been from him. Fuller in length, on middle and leg. Travis Head drives it past the diving mid on fielder and the ball races away to the boundary. He removes his helmet and soaks applause from his dressing room and the crowd erupts as well. Gets a hug from Mitchell Starc. He is elated. There were many questions regarding his place but he has repaid it by this ton. Sensational batting!
Short of a length, on the hips, Head flicks it on the leg side. Woakes runs across and collects it. A single.
A length ball, outside off. Starc shoulders arms.
Full and on middle. Starc looks to go big down the ground but ends up slicing it over covers for three runs.
A length ball, outside off. Head looks to defend but it takes the outside edge through the gully region and three runs are taken as the fielder chases it back and cuts it off.

OH DEAR! NASTY! Wood steams in and bowls a full toss, on middle, at 138.6 kph. Travis Head is completely taken aback by the bounce and is in no position to play that shot. The ball hits the gloves and then rolls up to hit his chin. He immediately goes down on the ground. Mark Wood walks up to him to see if he is okay. He looks to be in some pain though. Also, Mark Wood has overstepped and no ball has been given.
Length ball, on leg. Head looks to work it away but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller in length, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Head pushes it towards covers for a single.
THICK EDGE AND FOUR! Good-length ball, outside off. Starc looks to drive. The ball goes off the outside edge past the diving backward point fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller in length, on leg. Starc misses his flick. Gets hit on the pads. Wood with an half-hearted appeal for an lbw but the umpire is unmoved. That was going down the leg side.
Short of a length, on middle. Head pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, on middle. Head drills it to mid on.
On a length, on leg. Tucked on the leg side for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Driven to mid off.
Outside off, left alone by Starc.
Full and outside off. Starc lets it sail through.

Full and on the pads. Head flicks it to deep mid-wicket. Jack Leach from deep square leg chases it and keeps it down to three runs. The England players look very tired now and there body language says it all.
Outside off, left alone.

Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Starc looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Mark Wood appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. He is interested but Joe Root does not opt for a review.

Was there an inside edge there? Definitely some sound when the ball passed the bat. Good-length ball, on off, coming back in. Mitchell Starc has a swing at it but misses. The ball goes well away from the keeper and Jos Buttler does really well to dive to his right but fails to pouch it. Yup! HotSpot shows that there was an inside edge there.
Length ball, outside off. Starc shoulders arms.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Starc lets it go. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2!
Back of a length, on middle. Head stands up on his toes and plays it to gully.
Short of a length, on middle. Head hops and tucks it to square leg for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Starc leaves it alone. No signs of any swing as of now.
On a good length, outside off. Starc lets it go.
Length ball, on middle. Starc knocks it off the inside portion of the bat to deep square leg. Three taken. Australia now lead by 200 runs!
Fuller, outside off. Head drives it towards covers.
Good-length ball, angling away outside off. Starc lets it be.
Back of a length, on off. Starc taps it on the off side.
Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Mitchell Starc looks to flick but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length, on off. Starc taps it to point.
Fuller, on off. Starc chips it towards mid off for a single.
Pitched up, outside off. Head pushes it to point. Haseeb Hameed has a wild throw at the stumps for no reason. There is no one backing up and the batters take a single off the overthrows.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.
FOUR! He is continuing from where he left off! Short of a length, on middle. Head pulls it with disdain to deep square leg for a boundary.
Short of a length, on leg. Head looks to tuck. The ball goes off the thigh pad to the right of the keeper. The batters take a leg bye.
FOUR! Great shot! Fuller, on middle and leg. Starc works it away to wide of mid on for a boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Starc leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Starc looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to point.
Good-length ball, outside off. Head leaves it alone.
Length ball, on middle. Head blocks it on the leg side.
Full and outside off. Head drives it towards covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Head blocks it from the crease.
Length ball, outside off. Head dabs it past gully for a single.
Length ball, on leg. Starc pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Head hops and taps it to point.
Back of a length, outside off, at 141 kph. Head slashes it to deep point for a run.
On a length, on off. Starc defends it with ease.
On a length, on middle, at 145 kph. Starc defends it on the leg side.
Fuller this time, on off. Starc drives it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, on off. Starc hops and knocks it back to the bowler. These two are looking very solid!
Touch fuller, outside off. Head leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Short ball from Robinson, on middle. Head ducks under it and evades it comfortably.
Good-length ball, attacking the stumps. Head covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, angling away from off. Travis Head has a poke at it. The ball beats the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Short of a length, on middle. Head pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Back of a length, on off. Head jumps and defends it out off the inner half of the bat.
A length ball, outside off. Starc taps it to point.
A length ball, angling on the pads. Starc tucks it to deep square leg and collects a couple of runs.
Short of a length, on middle. Starc misses his flick as he closes his bat face early. Gets hit high on the pads.
On middle, on a length, hit back to the bowler.
Short stuff from Wood. Starc sits under it.
A length ball, on middle. Starc stays back and pushes it to Wood.
A length ball, on off. Head blocks it to covers.
A length ball, outside off, this one stays low and is too close for Head to cut it, misses.
A length ball, on off. Head dabs it to deep point for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Starc lifts it towards mid off who collects it on a bounce.
On the pads, this is flicked to square leg.
A length ball, outside off, this one nips back in. Starc looks to defend away from the body but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Short of a length, outside off, extra bounce as well. Head has a poke at it and misses it completely. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
A short of a length, outside off. Head hops and taps it to third man for a brace. Easy for Australia, no trouble whatsoever.
Length and angling on the pads. Head flicks it aerially and towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! More runs! A length ball, outside off. Starc gets an outside edge and the ball rolls away through the gully region for a boundary. It went through the diving fielder.
On middle, tucked away to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Head hops and blocks it out.
A length ball, on middle. Starc defends it off the front foot.
A low dipping full toss, on middle. Starc jams it out on the off side.
Short now, down leg. Easy leave for Starc.
A length ball, on middle. Starc is solid on his defense.
FOUR! Good shot! Pitches this one up, on middle. Starc drives it firmly through mid on for a boundary.
On middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, angling on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
SIX! Statement from Head! A full ball, on middle. Head smashes it straight down the ground for a biggie.
Short of a length, on middle. Head has to get on his toes to keep this one out.
Short and on middle, pulled away to square leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Starc blocks this one on the deck.
Another solid defense from Starc. 7 coming off it, an expensive start from Stokes.
Short of a length, around off. Head stays back and steers it to backward point for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Starc has a feel for it. The ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length, on leg. Starc defends it out from the crease.
FOUR! Starc is playing a gem of an innings here! Length ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc lofts it over mid on to fetch himself a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Starc lets it be.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, England get the breakthrough! Woakes hurls a length ball, on middle. Mitchell Starc flicks it towards deep square leg. Gets the height but not the distance. Rory Burns is stationed over there. He doesn't even have to move an inch. Keeps his eyes on the ball and takes it with ease. Mitchell Starc departs but Australia will feel he has done his job. Chris Woakes breaks the 85-run stand and now England will look to wrap things up.
Howout: c Rory Burns b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Good effort ball from Stokes! Serves a bumper, on off. Steep bounce on that occasion! Travis Head hops and takes his eyes off the ball. The ball goes off the outside edge to third man for a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Lyon hops and tucks it to square leg. Gets off the mark with a single but more importantly, hands over the strike to Head.
JUST SHORT! Short ball, on leg. Travis Head pulls it without any timing to deep square leg. Haseeb Hameed charges ahead from the deep to take the catch but the ball falls just short of him.
Another bouncer, on middle. Nathan Lyon looks to pull but misses.
And again! A short ball, down leg. Lyon looks to pull but once again fails to make any connection.
Length ball, on off. Lyon stays back and nudges it to mid on.
Length ball, on leg. Head tries to defend but gets hit on the pads. The ball drops on the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
On a length, on off. Lyon pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. That bounced sharply. Lyon looks to drive but misses.
On a good length, outside off. Lyon leaves it alone.
DROPPED! Fuller in length, outside off, nipping away. Nathan Lyon chips it to the left of Woakes. He extends his left hand and tries to catch it but the ball fails to stick in his palms.
Good-length ball, on middle and leg. Lyon looks to play across but gets hit on the pads. England appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no. Going down leg.
Length ball, on middle. Head tucks it on the leg side.
Length ball, down leg. Head tickles it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Lyon tries to pull but misses.

FOUR! Lyon takes on Stokes! Enough with the short balls, he says! Short of a length, on middle. Nathan Lyon pulls it to deep mid-wicket. Off the bottom of the bat but enough to clear the ropes. 400 up for Australia!
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Lyon again tries to pull. He misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller in length, on middle. Lyon drives it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Pulled to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, on middle. Flicked to deep square leg for a brace.
Good-length ball, angling in. Lyon knocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on off. Driven towards mid off.
Length ball, on middle. Lyon tucks it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Lyon lets it sail through.
Short and down the leg side. Head misses his flick.
Length again and down the leg side. Head steps across and misses his flick.
Third time missed. Length and down the leg side, this was close to the leg pole. Head shuffles way across and misses his tuck.
On a length, on off. Head hops and taps it to cover for a single.
Short of a length, on middle. Lyon swivel-pulls it through mid-wicket for three runs.
SIX! Just over the fielder! A length ball, angling on the pads. Head whips it away and just clears the square leg fielder for a biggie. 5 runs shy of 150.
A full ball, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Flatter and outside off. Lyon dabs it late past the first slip for a single.
Quicker now, spinning back in. Head blocks it out.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
A loopy ball, on middle. Lyon pushes it to mid-wicket.
In the air but safe. A length ball, on the pads. Head hops and flicks it uppishly and towards deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Edgy runs! Short of a length, on middle. Lyon rocks back and looks to pull but top-edges it over the keeper's head for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! Wood finally gets his man. Short ball, on middle. Lyon looks to pull but gets a leading edge high in the air and towards short square leg. Ollie Robinson charges in and takes a simple catch.
Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Mark Wood

Commentary: Short ball, on middle. Josh Hazlewood ducks under it.
Short ball again, on middle. Josh Hazlewood looks to block but gets hit on the gloves. No control on that shot and the ball drops safe on the deck.
A yorker now, on middle. Josh Hazlewood gets his bat down in time.

FOUR! 150 for Travis Head! What an innings this is from him. He gets all the applause and the Gabba crowd erupts to cheer him. A full ball, on middle. Head slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary and gets to his 150 in style.
Full again, outside off. Head tries to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off. Head mistimes his sweep to square leg for a quick single.
Full and outside off. Josh Hazlewood prods across and defends it to covers.
Tossed up, outside off. Hazlewood rocks back and blocks it out.
Full ball, outside off. Josh Hazlewood defends off the front foot.
Good-length ball, outside off. Took the pace off the ball. Travis Head looks to have a poke at it but drops his bat at the end.

DROPPED! That has been the story for England so far! Fuller this time, on middle, another off-pace delivery. Travis Head moves to the off side and flicks it uppishly towards deep mid-wicket. Haseeb Hameed charges ahead to take the catch. Dives in front but palms it out. The batters don't run though as Head wants to face as many deliveries as possible.

OUT! BOWLED! Finally, England get their man and end Australia's innings as well. Travis Head makes room for himself very early and exposes his stumps. Mark Wood fires a straight ball, on the stumps. Travis Head tries to carve it over covers but he backed way too far and the ball was out of his reach. It sends the stumps flying and Travis Head walks back to the pavilion on the back of an excellent knock. Australia finish with 425 and have a lead of 278 runs!
Howout: b Mark Wood

Commentary: Starts from around the wicket and gets a nice shape as he serves it on a length and on the pads. Hameed misses his flick and gets high on the pads.
Extra bounce there! Short of a length, around off. Hameed tries to shoulder arms but this one shoots of the deck and hits him near gloves. Good start from Starc.
A full ball, outside off. Hameed gets low and drives it firmly through point for three runs. England and Haseeb Hameed are underway.
An outswinger, on a length, outside off. Left alone.
Full ball, outside off, shaping away. Rory Burns punches it to point.

NOT OUT! Good review from Burns. A length ball, straight and on middle. Burns goes on the front foot as he looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Starc and Co. appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Burns thinks height might save him and takes the review. HotSpot shows no bat. Ball Tracker shows wicket missing and Burns guesses it right.
On a length, on middle. Hameed hops and blocks it out.
Back of a length, in the channel outside off. Hameed looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge. But falls just short to the first slip.
A length ball, on middle. Hameed keeps it out.
Short of a length, on middle. Hameed solidly blocks it.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length again, outside off. Hameed shoulders arms to it. Maiden to start for Josh Hazlewood.
Rory Burns is off the mark. A length ball, on the hips, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, angling outside off. Hameed sways away from it.
On the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
FOUR! First boundary of the second innings! A short ball, on middle. Burns pulls it nicely through square leg for a boundary. Total control on this shot.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle. Hameed defends it on the leg side.
Slightly short, outside off. Hameed looks to play at first but leaves it very late for the keeper to gobble it up.
Full and on off. Hameed pushes it off the inner half back to the bowler.
Angles it on the pads. Hameed misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
On a length, on off. Hameed with solid defense.
A length ball, outside off, with some extra pace. Hameed lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, outside off. Burns shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, on off. Burns hangs back and blocks it on the surface.
This was on a length and angling across, down the leg side. The ball clips the back leg and whizzes past the leg stump. Alex Carey does well to dive to his right and collect the ball.
Length and on the pads, flicked to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Both the openers settling in nicely now. A length ball, outside off. Hameed punches it through point for a boundary.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Good-length ball, on off. Burns blocks it from the crease.
Back of a length, on middle. Burns covers his sticks and blocks it out right under his eyes.
Length ball, slanting across. Burns covers the line and defends it watchfully.
Good-length ball, angling away, on off. Burns stays solid in his defence.
FOUR! First runs that Josh Hazlewood concedes this innings! Fuller, on the pads. Rory Burns tickles it to fine leg to collect a boundary.
Good-length ball, on middle. Blocked out.

Straight into the action! Short of a length, on middle, angling back in. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Haseeb Hameed is taken aback by the bounce. The ball goes off the gloves to square leg for a single.
Beautiful delivery! Good-length ball, around off, angling away. Rory Burns looks to defend but misses. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
On a good length, on middle. Burns is solid in his defence this time.
And again! On a good length, angling away from the left-hander, outside off. Rory Burns has a poke at it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.

In the air, but safe! Short of a length, on middle. Rory Burns pulls it over wide of square leg. Jhye Richardson there jumps and tries to catch but the ball goes over him into the deep for three runs.
Fuller, on off. Hameed drives it to cover for a single.
Short of a length, on off. Hameed looks to defend but plays it with soft hands. The ball goes off the outside edge to the slip cordon but dies out by the time the slip fielder could catch it.
On a good length, outside off. Hameed leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off. Hameed shoulders arms to that.
Full and on leg. Hameed works it on the leg side.
Bangs in short, on middle. Hameed ducks under it.
Good-length ball, on middle. Hameed covers the line, stands tall and defends it out with a dead bat. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Good-length ball, outside off. Burns lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, on middle, at 135 kph. Burns blocks it from his crease.
Fuller in length, at 136.8 kph, on off. Burns jams it out to the off side.
On a good length, outside off, nipping away. Burns tries to defend but misses. The ball was whiskers away from finding an outside edge.
Well outside off this time, an easy leave for Burns.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! First over after Lunch and Australia get the breakthrough and it is none other than the skipper who provides it. Bowls it on a good length, outside off. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Steep bounce and Rory Burns didn't expect that at all. He tries to cut it away but catches the gloves and carries it through to the keeper. Alex Carey makes no mistake behind the stumps and Rory Burns walks back to the pavilion. A wicket maiden from Pat Cummins!
Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Loopy ball, on off. Hameed works it with spin to short leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Hameed nudges it on the leg side for a run.
Quicker ball, around off. Malan defends it towards covers.
On middle, Malan plays it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Malan blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Malan looks to push but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one nips back in sharply, Short of a length, on middle. Haseeb Hameed shoulders arms but this one hits him on the body. Didn't see that coming.
On a length, on middle. Blocked out.
An appeal for LBW but turned down. Height might have saved Hameed. Angles a length ball, around off. Hameed misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Sharp bounce now. Short and on middle. Hameed ducks under it. The keeper leaps to grab it.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball and on middle. Hameed tucks it to mid-wicket. He shakes his head as he fails to beat the man there.
Short and outside off. Malan gets back and drives it to cover.
Intent from Malan. Comes down the track and pushes this full ball back to the bowler.
This one lands on middle and turns away sharply. Malan rocks back and leaves it alone. Sharp turn from Lyon.
Around off, blocked out.
Full and on the pads, this is flicked to square leg.
Slower one now, outside off. Malan punches it to covers and takes a quick single to get off the mark.
A length ball, angling outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
Again around off. Malan covers his stumps and lets it go.
Touch fuller, on off, pushed to mid off.
A length ball, outside off. Malan leaves it alone to the keeper.
Now serves a short ball, on middle. Malan sits under it.

EDGED! A length ball, slanting outside off. Malan looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge to the keeper. Alex Carey tries to take it low and on his left but it bounces just in front of him. Two taken as the ball rolls to fine leg.
Short and outside off. Hameed dabs it to backward point. Malan wanted a single but was sent back.
Full and on off. Hameed prods and blocks it.
Quicker one now, on middle. Hameed defends it under his eyes and the ball rolls back to the keeper.
Flatter and on middle. Kept out.
Full ball, outside off, tucked to mid-wicket.
A loopy ball, on off. Hameed knocks it to cover. A maiden!
FIVE WIDES! Extra bounce, extra pace and extra runs. A short ball, on middle. Malan sits under it. Carey leaps the highest but this one goes well over him to meet the fence.
On a length, on off, kept out.
An appeal for LBW but not given! A length ball, on middle. Malan misses his whip and gets hit on the pads. Pitching outside leg.
A length ball, across, outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
On the pads. Malan turns it softly on the leg side and takes a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Hameed prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Again prods and this time hits it off the middle to covers.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short and outside off. Malan rocks back and cuts it towards deep backward point for a boundary.
Full and on middle. Malan presses forward and defends.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan hangs back and cuts it to backward point.

OH! That was close! Lyon would have thought, he got his 400th Test wicket there! Tossed up, just above the off pole. Strange from Malan as he watches the ball and still lets it go. Nathan Lyon cannot believe that it didn't hit the off stump. Dawid Malan could consider him very lucky.
Outside off, Malan taps it towards point for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Hameed blocks it out.
FOUR! Short of a length, on off. Dawid Malan rides on top of the bounce and cuts it past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Malan taps it to point.
Fuller in length, Malan prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off. Malan shoulders arms to that one.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Good-length ball, on middle. Malan hops and defends it out.
Tosses it up, on middle. Hameed works it with spin on the leg side.
Full and on middle, Hameed presses forward to defend.
On middle, turning in. Hameed tucks it to square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Malan steers it to point.
Full and around off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Floated it up, on off. Malan punches it off the back foot through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed taps it on the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Hameed blocks it from the crease.
FOUR! Well played! Starc sprays this one down the leg side. Hameed tickles it to fine leg to collect a boundary.
Fuller, on the pads. Hameed flicks it to deep square leg. He pushes hard for the second run and gets it comfortably. Good running and that brings up 50 for England.
Back of a length, on off. Hameed hops and dabs it to the off side for a quick single.
On the pads again, flicked to deep square leg for a run.
Loopy ball, outside off. Malan cuts it to backward point.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan steps out and defends.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan blocks it out solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan is solid in his defence.
On the pads, defended to short leg. A maiden!
FOUR! Wayward from Starc! Full and down the leg side. Hameed tickles it fine to the fine leg fence.
Length ball, outside off. Hameed shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Good shot! A length ball, outside off. Hameed cuts it to backward point for a boundary.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Serves a short one now, on middle. Hameed sits under it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Bowling down the leg side has finally worked for Starc. A relief for Starc after been thrown for runs. This was on a length and down the leg side. Hameed tries to tickle it down the ground but manages only gloves on it. The keeper, Alex Carey pouches and celebrates straightaway as Hameed takes a long walk to the pavilion.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: A length ball, angling across, outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
A length ball, around off, in the corridor of uncertainty. Malan looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off. Malan hits it to covers.
On a length, on off. Malan defends this solidly.
A length ball outside off. Malan lunges and shoulders arms to it.
Short one now, outside off. Malan watches it sail to the keeper. Maiden.
A length ball, on middle. Root tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off, with extra pace. Root defends it off the front foot.
A length ball, angling on middle, pushed to mid on.
Slants it on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single. Joe Root is off the mark.

NOT OUT! A length ball, slanting outside off. Malan had an option to leave it but chases this wayward delivery. He has a poke at it but seems to miss it. Alex Carey catches it and appeals for it but nothing from the umpire. Australian players seem confident and Pat Cummins opts for the review. HotSpot shows no bat as the ball passes the toe end of the bat. The on-field decision stays. Australia lose their review.

A length ball, outside off. Malan prods and looks to defend but gets another edge just over the slip cordon and towards third man for three runs. Josh Hazlewood shakes his head as he knows this was a good delivery.
No run, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
A length ball, on the pads. Malan misses his flick and the ball clips the thigh pads on its way to the keeper who dives to his right to catch it.
Full and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Brilliant fielding from Starc, uses his long arms nicely. A full ball, on middle. Root on-drives it to the left of mid on where Starc dives and stops it.
Full again and on middle, Root nudges it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Root hops and taps it to point.
On a length, on off. Malan defends it under his eyes.
Length ball, angling across, outside off. Malan is beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend. Nice line from Josh Hazlewood.
On a length, outside off, nibbling away, left alone.
Fuller, around off, solidly defended by Malan.
Around middle and off, Dawid Malan goes back and works it towards square leg. Cummins gets across to stop to his left from wide mid on. A single taken.
A length ball, outside off, pretty wide, angling away, shouldered arms to.
Loopy ball, on leg. Malan clips it to square leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan defends it out.
Flatter on middle, Malan uses his feet to push it to mid-wicket for a single
Full and on off, Root defends it on the off side watchfully.
Drifting down leg, Root looks to tuck but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Nearly had him! Loopy ball, on off. Root looks to sweep but miscues. The ball goes off the top edge and falls over short leg.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Malan shoulders arms.
Again on a length, well outside off. Malan lets it be.
On a good length, around off, nipping away. Malan has a feel for it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Perfect delivery and perfect line from Hazlewood.
On a length, on off. Malan taps it on the off side.
Sprays this one down the leg side. Malan looks to flick but misses.
Full and on off, Root whips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Loopy ball, on middle. Root hangs back and defends it with a dead bat.
Full and around off, Root presses forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Root stays solid in his defence.
Around off, Root looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for an LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Loopy ball, on middle. Root works it on the leg side for a single.
On a good length, on off. Root watchfully blocks it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Root defends it off the back foot to the off side.
FOUR! Fuller, on middle. Root whips it through mid-wicket. Long chase for Jhye Richardson and he tries to push the ball back in but touches the boundary cushions in the process. A boundary!
Length ball, on middle. Knocked back to the bowler.
Fuller, on off. Driven back to the bowler.
On off, defended on the leg side.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan defends it out.
Full and on middle, Malan presses forward and defends it under his eyes.
Tossed it up, on off. Malan pushes it to mid off for a single.
Full and on off, Root steps out and flicks it uppishly to mid on for a single.
Allows the ball to spin and Malan pushes it towards covers.
Flighted delivery, on leg. Malan uses his feet and works it off the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket.
Starts with a length ball, down the leg side. Root lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, on middle. Root stays back and blocks it towards cover.
FOUR! EDGED! A full ball, outside off. Root looks to defend off the front foot but gets an outside edge between the slip cordon and the gully fielder and it races away to the fence.
A length ball, on off. Blocked out.
A full ball this one nips back, on off. Root lunges and looks to defend but gets an inside edge past the leg pole and towards deep backward square leg for a single. Root getting a bit edgy here.
A length ball, angling on the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Short ball, outside off. Root goes back and punches it to point for a quick single.
FOUR! Cut away! Short ball, outside off. Malan cuts it past point for a boundary.

A huge appeal for LBW but not given. A full ball, very full, angling on middle. Malan comes down the track and looks to whip but misses and gets hit on the boot. Lyon appeals but the umpire is not interested.
This is blocked out by Malan off the front foot.
FOUR! Full ball outside off. Malan drives it through covers and bags a boundary.
Flatter and on off. Malan keeps it out. An expensive over from Lyon, 9 coming off it.
A length ball, outside off. Root defends with an angled bat to point.
On a length and on middle. Root tucks it to mid on.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! A full ball, on off. Root drives it straight back to the bowler. Cummins tries to put his right foot across but fails and this one races away to the fence.
Short in length, Root works it on the leg side for a single.
Slanting on the pads, this is flicked through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! Boundaries flowing nicely for England. A short ball, outside off. Root rocks back and pulls it to mid-wicket for a boundary. 100 up for England as well.
Full and on middle, swept to square leg for a single.
Flatter, slower and outside off. Malan punches it to covers.
This one is bit quicker, outside off. Malan looks to punch it but misses.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan defends it on the deck.
Leg bye! A length ball, angling on middle. Root looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A muted appeal follows for LBW. Leg bye taken.
A short ball, on off. Malan thinks of pulling this but ends up tapping it on the leg side.
Short ball, on middle, pulled away to square leg for a single.
Short ball again and this time Root pulls it to square leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Malan gets beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend.
Short and on leg. Malan pulls it to the fine leg region for a single.
Flatter and outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Full and on middle. Malan blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan looks to defend but gets an outside edge and the ball rolls to point.
Quicker ball, outside off. Malan looks to cut but misses.
Around off, Malan is solid in his defence.
Given some loop, full and on middle. Malan prods and pushes it to mid on. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Back of a length, on middle. Root tucks it on the leg side.
Good-length ball, at 140.2 kph, on middle. Root blocks it from the crease.
Beauty from Starc! Good-length ball, on middle, coming back in. Joe Root gets all squared up and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller, outside off. Root lets it sail through.
On a good length, on leg. Root works it to square leg.
Short of a length, on off. Root hops and dabs it towards point. Looks like Mitchell Starc has found his rhytm back as he was very proving to be very expensive.  A maiden for him!
A full ball, on off. Malan defends it out.
Full and on middle, Malan uses his feet to push it towards covers.
Tosses it up, on off. Root presses forward to defend.
Slightly short, on middle. Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single. With that, he now has most runs in a calendar year, going past Michael Vaughan.
On off, Malan blocks it out off the front foot.
Loopy ball, on off. Malan stays solid in his defence.
Fuller, on off. Root drives it straight to covers.
Full again, outside off. Root drives it to mid off.
Short of a length, outside off. Root dabs it to gully.

FOUR! Shot! Fuller in length, outside off. Joe Root latches on it and drives it with an open face of the bat through covers. The ball races away to the boundary. 50-run partnership comes up between these two as well!
On a length, on leg. Root clips it to fine leg for a brace.
Good-length ball, outside off. Root leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Outside off, Malan pushes it past the diving extra cover fielder for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle. Root stays deep in the crease and tucks it on the leg side.
Tosses it up, on off. Root blocks it out.
Flatter ball, on middle, tucked on the leg side for a quick single.
Loopy ball, on off. Dawid Malan steps out and looks to defend. The ball hits the front pad and lobs up in the air. Nathan Lyon catches it with ease and puts up an appeal but that came off the pad.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
A length ball, slanting outside off. Left alone.
Outside off, on a length, Root leaves it to the keeper.
Very full, on off, pushed to mid off.
A length ball, extra bounce, on middle. Root looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. The ball drops back on the deck.
A length ball, outside off. Root taps it to point and takes a single.
FOUR! Ends the over with a boundary. A full ball, outside off. Malan looks to drive but this goes more off the splice through the gully region for a boundary.
Full and outside off. Root leans and drives it to covers.
FOUR! Full and way outside off. Root fetches and sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary. The square leg fielder runs across but to no avail.
Full and on off, defended out.
A flatter ball, on middle. Root tucks it to short leg.
On middle. Root wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
CLOSE! Lyon's wait for the 400th wicket continues. A flatter ball, outside off. Malan prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. A muted appeal only from the keeper follows.
On a length, outside off, blocked out.
A length ball, on middle. Root solidly blocks it.
FOUR! Pure timing! A length ball, on off. Root stays back and punches it wide of the diving mid off fielder for a boundary.
FOUR BYES! Bonus runs! A short ball, on middle. Root looks o ramp it over but misses. The keeper fails to catch it and it runs away for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Root hits it through point for a single.
Short again, around off. Malan sways away from the line of the ball.
A tossed up ball, on middle. Root blocks it out.
On middle, Root turns it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Both these batsmen are settled now! A full ball, on middle. Malan steps down and wrists it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on off, turning away. Dawid Malan looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to point.
Slightly short, outside off. Malan lunges and shoulders arms to it.
Loopy ball, outside off. Malan dabs it to backward point.
Extra bounce straightaway. A short ball, on middle. Root ducks under it. The keeper grabs it over his head.
Full now, on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on off. Root hops and taps it in front of covers for a quick single. Good running.
A length ball, outside off. Malan gets on his toes to defend but instead gets hit on the gloves. Green generating some bounce here.
A length ball, angling on the pads and going further away with the angle. Malan misses his flick. The keeper makes a full stretched dive to his right to grab it.
Short and on middle. Malan leaves it alone.
On middle, Root works it with spin to short leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Root presses forward and blocks it out.
Oh! That one stayed low! Tosses it up, around off. Joe Root looks to sweep but misses. The ball was inches away from hitting the off pole.

FOUR! FIFTY for the No.1 Test batsmen in the world! What a player! Short and outside off. Root gets into a better position this time and smashes it to deep mid-wicket. for a boundary. He raises his bat and soaks applause from the crowd. Has been a fighting knock from him after a first innings duck and England would want him to continue.
Tossed up, on off. Kept out.
Full and on middle, tucked away on the leg side.
Length ball, on middle. Malan clips it to square leg for a single.
Fuller, on middle. Root drives it wide of mid on for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Malan mistimes his pull to mid-wicket.
Sprays this one down leg. Malan looks to flick but misses.
On a good length, from 'round the wicket on middle. Malan prods and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Cameron Green appeals for an lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
Short of a length, outside off. Malan evades the line and lets it be.
Loopy ball, on middle. Root hangs back and tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Short and outside off, cut away to point for one. 150 up for England!
Floats it up, on middle. Root camps back and blocks it out.
Full and on middle, defended out.
Quicker, hurried onto the batter. Root rocks back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle, Root meets it with a dead bat.
Fuller in length, on off. Malan drives it towards extra cover.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan stands up on his toes and blocks it back onto the deck.
On a length, on middle. Malan tucks it around the corner.
Good-length ball, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Malan ducks underneath to this short ball.

FIFTY FOR MALAN! It has been a patien knock and this will do the world of good. Back of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan steers it nicely to third man. Long chase for the fielder and before the fielder cuts it off, the batters have run three. Raises his bat and gets appreciated by his skipper as well. Will look to convert this into a substantial score.
FOUR! Welcomes Marnus Labuschagne with a boundary. A short ball, on middle. Malan pulls it to short square leg where the fielder lets it through for a boundary. That was hit with power.
Short again, on middle, pulled again to deep mid-wicket for a single.
This is way outside off. Root chases and lets it be.
Tossed up, outside off. Root covers his stumps and allows it through.
Short and outside off. Root cuts it to point where the fielder fumbles and allows a single.
Full and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
On middle, eased down to mid on.
Full and on middle. Root flicks it nicely but straight to mid on.
On a length, on middle. Root stands tall and blocks it out.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Root ducks under it. The keeper does well to leap and grab it.
On a length on middle. Blocked out.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it with solidity and holds the pose for a while.
Full and on middle. Malan drills it down to long on for a single.
Full ball, outside off, pushed to deep covers for a single.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! A tossed up ball, spinning back into the left-hander. Malan looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. Might be spinning down.
Another shout for LBW but not given! Slightly short, outside off. Malan prods and pads it away.
Full and on middle, tucked to the leg side.
Full ball, Malan works  it to mid off for a single.
Full and outside off. Malan drives it to the right of covers for a single.
Angles it on a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Leg bye! Angles this one on the pads. Root misses his clip and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Full and on off, driven nicely but finds mid off.
Full and way down the leg side. Malan misses his flick.
FOUR! Nicely driven! A full ball, outside off. Malan caresses his drive through covers for a boundary.
This one spins away, outside off, pushed to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Malan lunges to defend it out.
Very full now, on off, drilled down to long on for one.
Again serves it full and outside off, pushed to deep covers for a single.
Darted on the pads, this is flicked to square leg for a single.
Width on offer, outside off. Root drives it to deep cover for one more.
On a length, outside off, tapped to backward point.
A length ball, outside off. Root watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
Around off, on a length. Root steps across and blocks it out.
A full ball, outside off. Root leans into his drive and eases it through covers. A long chase for Head and he cuts it off in the deep. Three.
Short and on middle. Malan pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Pitches it up, outside off. Root pushes it to covers and collects a brace.
Darted down leg, Malan looks to tuck but misses. The ball brushes off the pads and goes to fine leg. The batters take a couple of leg byes.
Full and on middle. Malan defends it out.
Full again, on middle. Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle. Malan uses his feet and looks to defend but gets hit on the back pad.
On off, pushed towards covers.
Close! Short and outside off. Malan looks to cut but misses.
Short of a length, on off. Root defends it more off the outer part of the bat to backward point.
Back of a length, on middle. Malan hops and taps it to point for a single.

OHHH! Back of a length, on middle. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Root is taken aback by the bounce. He hops and looks to defend. The ball hits his gloves. He goes down but gets up immediately. No harm done!
On a similar line and length, Root defends it right under his eyes.
Short of a length, on middle. Pulled to deep square leg for a single.

JUST SHORT! Short of a length, on middle. Malan pulls it towards backward square leg. Marcus Harris there misjudges and at the end dives ahead to take the catch but the ball drops just short. Probably because of the sun, Harris didn't see the ball at first.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle. Root stays solid in his defence.
Full and on leg, nudged to square leg.
On middle, tucked to square leg off the back foot for one.
Full and outside off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Malan steps out and blocks it out.
Back of a length, on off. Root stands tall and blocks it from the crease.
Fuller, on off. Root defends it on the off side.
Good-length ball, outside off. Root lets it be.
Short ball, outside off. Root sways away from the line and evades it.
Length ball, on off. Root presses forward and looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Marnus Labuschagne from the slip cordon appeals for an lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, kept out.
Full and on middle. Malan dances down the track and misses his defence. The ball hits him on the pads. Appeal for an lbw from Lyon but nothing from the umpire.
Down the leg side. Malan misses his tuck.
Outside off, Malan presses forward and punches it towards covers for a single.
Full and on off. Root blocks it out.
This is swept to backward square leg.
FOUR! Down the leg side again. Joe Root sweeps it past leg slip to fine leg for a boundary. That went right past Marnus Labuschagne at leg slip. Was hit too fast and went like a bullet.
FOUR! Punished! A length ball, way outside off. Malan cuts it with ease past point for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Malan dabs it to gully.
A short ball, down the leg side. Malan keeps it out.
Back of a length, on middle, pulled away to deep square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Root punches it straight down the ground and collects two before the mid on fielder cuts it off.
Around off. Root hops and taps it to covers for a quick single.
A full ball, outside off. Root punches it to covers. A single was available but opts not to take it.
FOUR! Improvisation! A full ball, outside off. Root reverse sweeps it through the first slip and bags a boundary.
Tossed up, outside off, Root pushes it to covers for a single.
Tossed up again. Malan defends it on the deck. Marnus Labuschagne at short leg appeals but nothing from the umpire.
On middle. Blocked out.
Slightly short, on off. Malan punches it to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Root steers it to the fifth slip who carries it on a bounce.
Length and on off. Root blocks it out.
Serves a short ball, on middle. Root sits under it.
A length ball, on middle. Defended out.
Length and on off. Root dabs it late and towards gully.
A length ball, outside off. Root guides it to short third man for a single.
Full ball, on off. Root leans and blocks it out.
Around off. Root again plays the reverse sweep but this time finds backward point.
Shorter and on off. Root works it to covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Root dead bats it.
Slightly short and outside off. Root cuts it late and towards third man for a brace.
On middlle, Root wrists it to deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, on off. Root defends it under his eyes and to the off side.
Short of a length, on off. Root gets on his toes and taps it late to gully.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Root leans back and lets it go.
Leg bye! A length ball, on the pads, Root misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but that was clearly pitching outside leg. Leg bye.
Short in length, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length, on middle. Malan mistimes his pull towards short mid-wicket where the ball drops in front of the fielder. An opportunity after a very long time.
Length ball, on off. Root blocks it from his crease.
Fuller, on the pads. Root flicks it to deep square leg for a brace.
Full and on off, knocked back to the keeper.
Short ball, on middle. Root ducks under it.

Short of a length, on leg. Root tucks it on the leg side for a single. 150-run partnership between these two. They have shown tremendous will power and grit and determination. They give each other a little pat on the back as well.
Back of a length, outside off. Malan guides it to third man for one.
Bangs in short, on middle. Malan ducks under it.
Length ball, outside off. Malan chases after it and swings his bat but misses.
Short again, on middle. Malan sits under it again.
Back of a length, on off. Malan taps it to point.
On a good length, on middle. Malan defends it out.
Short of a length, on middle. Malan pulls it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Good-length ball, outside off. Malan chases after it again but fails to make any connection.
Bangs in short, outside off. Malan sways away from the line.
Outside off, steered to deep point for a brace.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
This is dabbed to gully off the back foot.
Full and on off, driven through covers for a single.
FOUR! Nice shot! Fuller, outside off. Dawid Malan drives it through covers for a boundary.
Full and on middle. Malan blocks it out.
Given some flight, on middle. Malan pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Malan backs away and looks to cut but misses. 7 balls left to end the day, why would you play that shot? Quiet risky from Malan there.
Tossed up, outside off. Malan leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Root taps it to point.
Fuller, driven back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Root hops and taps it on the off side. Malan is keen for a single but is sent back by his skipper.
Bangs it short, on leg. Root ducks under it.
On middle. Root watchfully blocks it.

Heart in mouth for England fans! Good-length ball, around off. Joe Root covers his line and has a feel for it. The ball whizzes past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Australia put up an appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Root at the end does well to survive the last ball. England trail by 58 runs. This has been a great turnaround for them. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Cummins starts with a length ball, outside off, curling away a bit. Dawid Malan shoulders arms to it. A bit of a lifeless delivery, not carrying to the keeper.
Another ball, on a length, just outside off and going on with the angle. Dawid Malan prods but does not offer any shot to this one. This time there is good carry to Carey.
Good-length delivery, around off. Dawid Malan presses forward and blocks it towards cover.
Back of a length, around the fourth stump channel. Dawid Malan stays back and leaves it alone.
Cummins changes the angle and comes from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. Dawid Malan lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, outside off. Dawid Malan lets it through to the keeper. A maiden over to start with!
Flatter ball, on middle, Joe Root hangs back and nudges it wide of square leg for a run. England are underway on Day 4!
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dawid Malan stays back to cut but finds the backward point fielder.
Tossed up, on middle, Dawid Malan skips down and tucks it to mid-wicket. Pat Cummins there dives and makes a half-stop, preventing the single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dawid Malan drives it to the cover fielder.
A bit quicker this time, on a length, outside off. Dawid Malan stays back and leaves it alone. A brave one, that wasn't too far away from the off pole.
Tossed up, on a fuller length, outside off. Dawid Malan presses forward and drives it to extra cover for a run. Malan is up and running on Day 4!
Good-length ball, around off. Malan prods, covers the line of the ball and taps it towards the gully fielder.
Length ball, angling in from off, Malan gets forward and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Dawid Malan prods to defend but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards the backward square leg region. The batters cross for a run.
Back of a length, nipping back in slightly from off. Root gets behind the line of the ball and defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery, around the fourth stump line. Root stays back and blocks it out watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Root stays back, opens the face of his bat to run it past the slip cordon but Cameron Green at gully dives to his left to stop the ball.
Tossed up, around off. Dawid Malan blocks it out off the front foot.
Flatter ball, around middle. Malan skips down and looks to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. Luckily for him, the ball does not pop out towards the silly point fielder.
Flatter ball, on off. Dawid Malan stays back and pushes it to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally! Finally! Nathan Lyon has scaled the mountain of 400 wickets in Test cricket, it has been an arduous climb, to be honest, as Lyon had to spend extra time in preying that elusive one wicket. He is only behind two greats, Shane Warne and Glenn McGrath, in the list of the leading wicket-takers for Australia in Test cricket. From being a pitch curator at the Adelaide Oval to becoming only the 7th spinner in Test cricket history to do so after the famous six - Muttiah Muralitharan, Shane Warne, Anil Kumble, Rangana Herath, Harbhajan Singh and Ravichandran Ashwin, it's been one heck of a ride. Now coming to the delivery, it's nicely flighted and around off, Dawid Malan takes a step down the track and tries to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It lobs up and Marnus Labuschagne reacts quickly from silly point to catch the ball. They all appeal and the finger has gone up. Something similar happened on the second ball of this over as well but then Dawid escaped. Not this time. Early exit for him this morning and it's a perfect start for Australia. 326 days between 399 and 400 wickets. That was a long wait. Lyon takes the ball and shows it to the audience to celebrate his milestone. Take a bow, GOAT!
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Flatter ball, on a length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Ben Stokes presses forward to block this one out.
Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root stays back and guides it towards deep backward point for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders arms to this one.
Green goes fuller this time, but the line is way outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Ben Stokes gets right behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
Fuller in length this time, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it hard but finds the cover fielder.
FOUR! Ben Stokes is off the mark! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away a bit. Stokes hangs back, opens the face of his bat and guides it past the diving gully fielder for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Root stays back and taps it wide of backward point for a quick run.
Tossed up, around off. Ben Stokes defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Tossed up, on a fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes looks for a slog-sweep but he misses as the ball goes past his blade.
Lyon follows it up with an arm ball, around leg, Ben Stokes stays back to block but he misses and gets hit on his pad.

A stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Loopy ball, on a length, around off. Ben Stokes gets forward to block but gets an inside edge onto his pad. Lyon consults with his mates for a review but they decide to go against it.
Flatter ball, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Huge blow to England as both the overnight batters are back in the hut very early with the second new ball due soon! It is Cameron Green who gets the big fish and Joe Root is denied his maiden hundred on Australian soil. This was a good-length delivery, around the fifth stump. It's an outswinger. Root has a tentative poke at it and it takes the outside edge towards Alex Carey behind the sticks who takes a simple catch. The Aussies are pumped and England are in a spot of bother now! They trail by 49 runs.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards the gully region.
Banged into the deck, around middle, Pope ducks underneath watchfully.
Good-length ball, around off. Ollie Pope defends it to covers.
Back of a length, around off. Ollie Pope gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
FOUR! A gift from Green and Pope does not miss out! Green sprays it down leg. Pope clips it off his pads and the ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Tossed up, on off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Stokes punches it to the cover-point fielder who half-stops it and the batters collect a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! What is happening here? England lose another and they have lost their third wicket in the space of just 14 runs this morning! With the monkey off his back, Nathan Lyon is bowling with a nice rhythm. Gives this one some extra toss and lands it close to off, it has got good revs and there is an excellent grip for him as the ball lands and turns in with some extra bounce. Pope stays back and looks to cut but the bounce gets big on his bat and it takes the shoulder of his blade before hurrying to Steven Smith at first slip. He takes a sharp catch by stretching to his right and Australia are smelling blood.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Flatter and quicker, around off. Jos Buttler hangs back and blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Jos Buttler defends it out towards cover.
Flatter ball, outside off, going on with the angle. Buttler stays back to block but it beats the outside edge.
Full ball, outside off. Ben Stokes prods but shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length, just outside off. Stokes hangs back and lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, angling in from outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Sloppy from the cover fielder but no harm done! Full ball, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it to the cover fielder who fumbles but Stokes does not go for a single.
A yorker, around off. Stokes gets his bat down in time and digs it out.
Back of a length, outside off and nipping back in slightly. Ben Stokes lets it through to the keeper.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Jos Buttler stays back to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
FOUR! Intent from Jos Buttler! This is tossed up, outside off. Buttler gets forward and reverse-sweeps it past the backward point fielder to collect a boundary. He is off the mark in some style.
Flatter ball, shorter in length, around off. Jos Buttler waits for the ball to turn and tucks it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on a fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Ben Stokes gets forward and keeps it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Ben Stokes prods and pushes it to covers.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it to the off side.

Beaten all ends up! This is the reason Australia have not opted for the second new ball. Green is getting the old one to move around. A gentle outswinger, landing around off and shaping away a bit, Jos Buttler feels for it and gets beaten.
A touch short and on off, Jos pushes it from the back foot to covers.
Pitches it up and close to off, Buttler is forward with a straight bat and pushes it down to mid on.
Plays late and plays well. Around off on a length, moving away a bit, Jos plays close to his body and eases it with an angled bat to cover-point for one.
Green switches to 'round the wicket and hurls across a length ball wide outside off, an easy leave for Stokes.
Flighted and full, around off, Jos Buttler is not shying away from playing the reverse-batted shot. Connects and sends it through backward point for a single.
FOUR! Bang! Loopy and full around off, Stokes goes down on one knee and sweeps it well in front of square leg for a cracking boundary.
Tossed up and around off, Stokes stays back and defends it to the off side.
Gets forward to a full ball and defends it to silly point.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it with soft hands to silly point.
Starts with a fuller one, shaping in, Buttler helps it to square leg for a single.
Back of a length around off, Stokes pushes at it and misses.
Starc goes fuller and lands it outside off, Stokes attempts to drive but misses.
Fullish and on off, driven off the front foot to mid off.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping away, Stokes allows it through.
FOUR! Boom! Width on offer, full in length, Stokes latches onto it and smashes it through covers for a boundary. The deficit is below 30 runs now.
In the channel outside off, Buttler shoulders arms.
A touch short and outside off, not much movement, Buttler once again gives it the silent treatment by leaving it alone.
Angling in and hitting Buttler on the pads. It deflects to gully.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works it gently to mid-wicket.
Extra bounce, Buttler tries to fend it away but it goes off the thigh pad to gully.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone.
A lifter, striking Stokes on his gloves as he attempts to glance. It rolls behind square leg and they cross.
Pitches it up and around off, Jos pushes it off his front foot to mid off.
On the pads, helped wide of mid on for one.
A touch short and outside off, left alone.
Outside off, on a length, Ben makes another leave.
Shortish, outside off, shaping away, Buttler leaves.
FOUR! Edged! Buttler tries defending off the front foot but it takes the outside edge and finds the gap between the slip cordon and gully.
Presses forward and works it with the angle of the bowler to mid-wicket.
Outside off, defended to point.
Beaten! Buttler tries driving off the front foot but misses.
FOUR! Length ball, outside off, steered through backward point for a boundary.
Outside off, no shot offered.
A touch short and on off, defended down to gully.
Play and a miss! Full and outside off, Ben Stokes is beaten while attempting to drive.
Shortish, targeting the body, Stokes tries to fend but misses. It goes off his pads to short leg.
On a length and outside off, played down to point.
Back of a length, on middle, worked to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Well timed and placed. Josh Hazlewood overpitches outside off, Jos Buttler leans into the drive and caresses it square of the wicket on the off side. Nathan Lyon chases from point but to no avail.
On a good length, around off and angling in, Buttler defends it from the back foot.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Jos tucks it towards long leg and rotates the strike.
Bowls it a touch short and keeps it close to off, Stokes remains on the back foot and defends it down.
Josh Hazlewood goes fuller this time, around middle and off, Buttler takes a couple of steps down the track and defends it to mid off.
Angling away from the batsman, around off and moving away slightly, Stokes guards his stumps and shoulders arms.
Cummins hits the deck hard and immediately gets some extra lift. Around off and Buttler does well to defend it down.
Extra bounce again, around middle and leg, Buttler leaps on the back foot and tucks it down to fine leg for a single.
Arrows a length ball around off, angling away, Stokes stays on the back foot and defends it very late near his body.

OUT! That's a snorter and Pat Cummins has taken out Ben Stokes. The sixth wicket goes down for England and they still trail by 12 runs. Once again the extra bounce that Cummins generates has done the trick. He is a beast with the new ball. Lands it around leg and gets it to jump a tad extra off the deck. Stokes is squared up slightly in his stance as he tries to work it on the leg side but closes the face of his bat early. The ball lobs off the leading edge and Cameron Green grabs the catch safely at gully. The replays show that it took the shoulder of his bat. The Aussies are ecstatic, England's talisman is gone.
Howout: c Cameron Green b Pat Cummins

Commentary: The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Cummins digs in a bouncer, Woakes ducks. End of a successful over for the Aussie skipper.
Back of a length, around off and angling in, Buttler defends it from the back foot.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and offers a dead straight bat in defense.
In the zone outside off, short in length, Buttler restrains himself from going after the width.
Almost edges it behind! That's a terrific delivery. Josh Hazlewood probes around the off stump area and it skids on with the angle with some extra bounce, Buttler pokes at it and misses.
This one is darted in, on a length and around off, Buttler covers the angle and defends it back.
On a good length around off, Jos sticks on the back foot and defends it with soft hands to point.

Was there any bat on it? Was it too high? Cummins consults his mates for the DRS and decides to go against it. A good-length ball, around off and nipping back in sharply. Chris Woakes is stuck in his crease as he tries to block it but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. Cummins appeals but the umpire says no. The Hawk Eye confirms that the ball would have gone over the sticks. The good thing about Pat Cummins is that he considers a few facts before deciding to use the review, unlike a few others.
Length ball, around off. Chris Woakes blocks it out.
Edged but safe! On a length and outside off, Woakes has a poke at it and edges it behind towards gully. It doesn't carry and Green does well to stop it with a dive to his left.
Short and down the leg side, Woakes tries glancing but misses. A terrific take by Alex Carey.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes stays back to block it but it goes off the outer half of the blade past the gully fielder. The batters take a couple of runs.
Good-length ball, around off. Chris Woakes blocks it out towards covers.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh, dear! Nothing has gone England's way this morning and Australia are bossing this game! Hazlewood serves a good-length ball, outside off, shaping away a hint off the seam. Buttler has a needless poke at it away from his body and it takes the outside edge towards Alex Carey behind the sticks who takes a simple catch, his 7th in this Test match so far. England lose their seventh wicket and they still trail by 10 runs.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Josh Hazlewood

Commentary: Length ball, angling in from middle. Ollie Robinson defends it towards mid on.
BEATEN! Back of a length, just outside off, shaping away a bit and bouncing off the deck. Ollie Robinson looks to have a tentative push but he misses as the ball whistles past his blade.
Short of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson stays back and taps it to the right of the gully fielder. Cameron Green there dives across to his right and stops the ball. A single taken.
FOUR! Nicely done! Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes stays back, rides the bounce well and steers it past the point fielder to collect a boundary. The deficit is 5 now.
Length ball, angling in from outside off. Chris Woakes leaves it alone.
Cummins bends his back and bangs it into the deck, around middle. Ollie Robinson ducks underneath.
Sharp bounce! Short of a length, outside off. Ollie Robinson looks to block but it hits the shoulder of his bat and rolls towards the gully fielder.
Funny! Full ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson anticipates a bumper so he thinks of ducking underneath first and leaves it alone in the end. Very awkward.
A well-directed bumper, around off. Ollie Robinson ducks yet again.

Top delivery! A length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Ollie Robinson looks to defend but the ball sneaks through his defense and brushes his back pad before going to the keeper. Alex Carey collects the ball, appeals but the umpire shakes his head.
Good-length ball, around off. Ollie Robinson blocks it out.
Good-length ball, around off. Chris Woakes looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the gully fielder, on the bounce.
Back of a length, around middle, Chris Woakes defends it to mid on.
Hazlewood goes full this time, outside off. Woakes pushes it to mid off, off the back foot.

Full ball, around middle. Chris Woakes plays the on drive but Pat Cummins puts in a dive at mid on to save a certain boundary. Since it's not a clean stop as the ball wobbles out of his hands, the batsmen get the chance to take a single.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Ollie Robinson defends it out.
A well-directed bumper, around middle. Ollie Robinson backs away and sways away from the line of fire by taking his eyes off the ball.
Banged in into the deck, just outside off. Chris Woakes tried fending it off but missed.
Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes sits back and blocks it towards covers.
Short of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes hangs back and opens the face of his bat to steer it away from the slip cordon but he finds the gully fielder.

FOUR! Edged, but safe! Good-length ball, just outside off. Chris Woakes looks to push inside the line but gets a genuine outside edge which goes in between the gully and second slip fielders for a boundary. England have cut down the deficit and are effectively 0 for 7.
Good-length ball, on off. Chris Woakes pushes it to mid off.
Cummins hurls a well-directed bumper, around off. Chris Woakes ducks under it at first then tries to ramp it over the keeper but he misses.
Flatter and quicker, around middle, Ollie Robinson blocks it out.
Tossed up, on a fuller length, around off. Ollie Robinson skips down to slog but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards deep mid-wicket for a run. England lead by 1 run now!
Flatter and quicker, around middle, Chris Woakes pushes it to mid-wicket.
Another ball, flatter and quicker, around off. Chris Woakes keeps it out.
Lyon spills this one down leg. Chris Woakes lets it be and Alex Carey moves across to his left to gather the ball.
Slightly shorter in length, around middle and turning in late. Chris Woakes drops it in front of short leg.
Full ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson hangs back and drives it past the mid off fielder. The fielder at mid off gives it a chase and the batters take three runs.
Length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes reaches out and looks for a booming drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler.
Length ball, angling in from middle, Chris Woakes presses forward and blocks it out.
Banged into the pitch, outside off. Chris Woakes leaves it alone.
A well-directed bouncer, around leg. Chris Woakes dabs it into the deck.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off and angling away with the arm of the bowler. Chris Woakes looks to drive on the up but he misses as the ball zips past the outside edge.
Tossed up, around off. Ollie Robinson defends it out.
Tossed up, around off. Ollie Robinson shimmies down to slog but it goes off the thick inside edge past the short fine leg fielder. Mitchell Starc gives it a chase and the batters take three runs.
Flatter ball, outside off and spinning in late. Chris Woakes blocks it off the back foot.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Chris Woakes eases it to long on for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ollie Robinson tries to get creative but he perishes in doing so! Lyon cleverly tosses this one up, outside off. Robinson looks to play the reverse sweep but does not nail it and hits it straight to Travis Head at backward point who takes a good sharp catch. England lose another and they lead by just 8 runs in the second innings.
Howout: c Travis Head b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Flatter ball, around off. Mark Wood defends it off the back foot.
Full ball, outside off. Chris Woakes looks to play the cover drive but it goes off the inside edge past the leg stump and the batters sneak in a run.
Banged into the deck, around leg. Mark Wood looks to block but it goes off his gloves behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Chris Woakes drives hard but Travis Head at covers dives to his left and stops the ball.
Short of a length, on middle. Chris Woakes gets behind the line to block.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes stays back and steers it behind square on the off side for a run.
A bouncer, around middle. Mark Wood gets behind the line and keeps it out. The ball pops out but falls well short of the short leg fielder.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Chris Woakes defends it out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Chris Woakes blocks it.
Loopy ball, way outside off. Chris Woakes defends it to covers.
Flatter and quicker, around middle, Chris Woakes sits back and eases it past the diving mid on fielder to collect a single.
Shorter in length, around middle, Mark Wood blocks it watchfully.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Mark Wood presses forward to block but it goes off the inside edge past the short leg fielder.
Starc steams in from 'round the wicket and hurls a length ball outside off at 142.7 clicks, Wood sits back and plays a mistimed shot to the off side.
That's a rip-roaring bouncer. Starc clocks 142.3 kph and dishes out a nasty bouncer around middle, it's well-directed, Wood fails to move away from the line of fire and takes a blow on his gloves.
FOUR! Wood has decided to fight fire with fire. Short in length again but there is some width offered outside off, Wood stays back and ramps it down to third man for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, driven through the line to mid off.
Bouncer, nicely directed this time, around middle and leg, Wood immediately takes cover and ducks.
Yet another bouncer, slightly wayward this time as it's angling down the leg side, Wood has a comfortable leave on this occasion.
Full and floated, around off and spinning in, Woakes defends it with his bat in front of his front pad.
Loopy and around off, turning back in, Woakes tries to defend off the front foot but it takes the inside edge and rolls wide of short leg. They cross.
Flighted and on off, defended from the crease by Wood.

OUT! TIMBER! A classic off spinner to dismiss Mark Wood. A generously tossed up delivery around off, plenty of drift on this one as it lands full and around off, Wood is lured into the drive but it beats the outside half of his bat and goes on to tickle the off pole. Lyon has a 4-fer now and England one wicket away from getting bundled out. They are ahead by just 18 runs.
Howout: b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Spinning away from around off, Leach lets it through to the keeper.
Beaten! Drift again for Lyne, he lands it just outside off and gets it to skid in, a late decision by Leach to cut but he misses.
Wide! A gentle bouncer and it has gone way over the head of the batsman. Called a wide for height.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and taps it down to square leg.
Back of a length around off, Woakes pushes it from the back foot to the off side.
On a length around off, Chris pushes it with soft hands to cover-point.
Around middle and leg, on a length, Woakes keeps it out to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, slanting in, Woakes defends it from the back foot to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Superb delivery, Green follows the batsman with a well-directed short ball at 138.3 kph, Woakes leans back and attempts to play the upper-cut but only manages to edge it to Alex Carey. He claims his 8th catch of this Test match. What a debut for him! He equals Brian Taber and Chris Read who also had eight wicket-keeping dismissals on Test debut. England are bundled out for 297 with a lead of only 19 runs.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: NO BALL! Robinson starts with a good-length ball, on off, Alex Carey blocks it to covers and looks for a run but is sent back by Marcus Harris. Robinson oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
Good-length ball, outside off and shaping away a bit. Alex Carey looks to poke at it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Back of a length, way outside off. Alex Carey prods and shoulders arms to this one.
On a length, around off. Alex Carey gets behind the line of the ball to block it.
Short of a length, way outside off and angling away late. Alex Carey does not offer any shot to this one.
JAFFA! Good-length ball, pitching around off and curling away sharply. Carey sits back and looks to drive but he misses as the ball goes past the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Alex Carey looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge behind square on the leg side. The batters cross for a single. Carey gets off the mark.
Woakes starts with a length ball, around middle, Alex Carey presses forward and defends it solidly.
Back of a length, around leg. Alex Carey looks to tuck it to the leg side but he misses and gets hit high on his body.
Good-length ball, around off and angling in just that little but. Alex Carey keeps it out.
Woakes hurls a good-length ball, around leg. Carey stays back and glances it to the left of the fine leg fielder. Ollie Robinson there cuts it off and the batters take a run.

NOT OUT! An inside edge saves Marcus Harris! Length ball, pitching around middle and nipping back in slightly. Harris looks to defend but fails to do so cleanly. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but the finger stays down. Joe Root decides to review it but the Hot Spot detects a spot on the bat.
Back of a length, outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
Length ball, on off. Alex Carey taps it to covers and takes off for a run. Haseeb Hameed at cover-point collects the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marcus Harris leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off and angling away late. Marcus Harris shoulders arms to this one. No ball signalled by the umpire as Ollie Robinson oversteps.
Full ball, around leg. Marcus Harris clips it to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, around off. Alex Carey pushes it to mid off.
Good-length ball, on off. Alex Carey defends it off the front foot.

Run out chance missed! Good-length ball, way outside off. Alex Carey lifts it over the cover region. Haseeb Hameed, at covers, gives it a chase and stops the ball by sliding just in front of the fence. The batters take three runs. Carey wants three and would have been a goner had Ollie Robinson collected the throw from the deep cleanly.
Length ball, outside off and staying a touch low. Alex Carey looks to block but he misses.
Back of a length, around middle. Alex Carey tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Alex Carey prods to block this one out.
Back of a length, around middle. Alex Carey nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, angling in from middle. Alex Carey tucks it wide of mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, outside off. Carey looks for a booming drive but it goes off the inner half of the blade back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Marcus Harris blocks it out watchfully.

Nicely done! Short of a length, just outside off. Marcus Harris stays back, rides the bounce well and punches it past the point fielder. The fielder at point chases it down and the batters take three runs.
Full ball, darted on the pads. Carey clips it towards the deep backward square leg fielder and rotates the strike.
Good-length ball, on off. Marcus Harris blocks it to mid-wicket.
Robinson goes fuller again, around leg. Marcus Harris flicks it to deep square leg and collects a run.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ollie Robinson gets his man and it won't be a 10-wicket win for Australia. Ollie Robinson keeps probing around off, on a length and nipping away a bit, Carey doesn't show much footwork as he looks to poke at it and gets a faint tickle towards Jos Buttler. He takes a simple catch.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: FOUR! There it is! Marcus Harris scores the winning runs for Australia! Fuller in length, outside off. Harris gets low and drives it behind square on the off side to collect a boundary. Harris fist-pumps and Australia win by 9 wickets!
